title: grandma lombardi's ravioli
directions: Mix together as regular dough.
Fill with filling mixture as noted below.
Cook ravioli in water with oil so they do not stick together and a little chicken broth until done.
Keep warm on plate in oven.

title: party chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the ingredients.
(Chicken should be cooked prior as well as the broccoli.)
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Use juice and rind of lemons.
Beat whole eggs.
Add sugar gradually and beat well after each.
Add lemon rind and juice. Add butter.
Cook over boiling water until mixture thickens.

title: creole vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil, in blender and blend well.
Slowly dribble in oil while blending until all is combined. Good over salads or as a dressing on shrimp cocktail.
Especially good with fresh home grown tomatoes.

title: frances bailey's coconut cake
directions: Add Crisco and sugar to dry ingredients.
Mix according to directions on box and bake.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: In skillet, cook bacon and drain.
Using 2 tablespoons of bacon grease, cook onions.
Stir in flour.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir
in water (or juice), vinegar and sugar.
Heat until bubbly.
Add beans and heat until slightly thick.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix eggs, flour and sugar, then mix the rest of the ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes at 400°, then for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine brown sugar, syrup, salt and butter.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Continue to cook over medium heat 5 minutes without stirring.
Add vanilla.
Place popcorn in large baking pan.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn.
Heat in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Pour on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: granola cookie bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla and water.

title: easy orange cake
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely and frost.

title: grandma ruby's glorified rice
directions: While rice is still warm, mix in pineapple and marshmallows. Whip cream and fold in; mix well.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread rolls on large cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown. Cool.
Mix cream cheese and dressing mix; spread on crust.
Add very finely chopped veggies.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place in a 450° oven only until cheese is slightly melted.

title: coconut pie
directions: Boil mixture until thick.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour mixture into cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: one-pan blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Melt margarine into an 11 x 7-inch baking pan. Add milk, biscuit mix and sugar. Stir until smooth. Drop spoonfuls of filling over batter. Bake 30 to 35 minutes until deep golden brown.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut each unpeeled potato into 8 pieces.
Combine melted oleo with the rest of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and toss until potatoes are covered with mixture.
Place potatoes on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 40 minutes.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Place pineapple in a small bowl and toss with 1/4 cup rum. Refrigerate, covered, for several hours.

title: kansas hot dog relish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large kettle.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 3 hours, then drain.
Combine vinegar and sugar in saucepan; heat and then add to cucumber mixture.
Tie spices and seeds in a bag; add to the kettle.
Bring to a boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Place in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Yield:
7 pints.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses in medium bowl with electric mixer on medium speed.
Shape cheese mixture into ball; roll in pecans. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve as a spread with crackers.

title: carrot salad or copper pennies
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots.
Do not overcook.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, soup, dry mustard, salt and pepper in saucepan. Heat until sugar is melted, but do not boil.
Mix all vegetables with the sauce.
Best made 24 hours before using.

title: taffy apple salad with peanuts
directions: Combine pineapple juice with sugar, flour, vinegar, egg and peanut butter.
Cool completely.
Spoon from saucepan into large bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip, add pineapple, nuts and apples.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Can easily be doubled.
When doubled it fills the Tupperware Fix & Mix Bowl.

title: poached rainbow trout(135 calories per serving)
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, reserve 1 (4-inch) piece of green onion for garnish.
Thinly slice remaining onions (about 1/4 cup).
In a 12-inch skillet over high heat, heat sliced green onions, Sauterne, garlic, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and 1/2 cup water to boiling.
Add 3 trout and heat to boiling.
(If using fresh trout, cook all at once.)
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop meat (reserving 1/2 package).
Mix all ingredients together and shape into ball.
Press reserved meat on outside of ball.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in pumpkin, oil, eggs and water.
Fold together well; add raisins.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° until done when tested, about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken livers
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserve drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside; keep warm.
Add livers to skillet and saute 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Add reserved bacon, mushrooms, green onions, wine, water and bouillon cube.
Cook 5 minutes or until bouillon cube is dissolved and mixture is heated, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: gold punch
directions: Mix equal parts of juice and ginger ale.
Serve ice cold.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and spices.
Add pumpkin mix.
Stir in milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 425° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: broiled chicken livers
directions: Cut bacon strips in half; quarter chestnuts.
Marinate bacon and chestnuts in soy sauce.
Cut chicken livers in small pieces. Wrap 1 piece chicken liver and 1 piece chestnut with bacon strip. Secure with toothpick.
Broil until bacon is browned.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in 1 1/2-quart (medium) bowl on High 1 minute.
Stir well.
Microwave 1 minute longer.
Stir until chocolate is melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla, salt and walnuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Resift with soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add rolled oats.
Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Stir in well beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture in thirds alternately with third of the milk.
Stir well after each addition.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic to flavor oil. Take garlic out.
Cook chicken in oil until light brown on both sides. Place in baking dish. Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil. Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove foil.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken. Cook until cheese melts.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Beat together all ingredients except nuts.
Shape into a ball. Roll in nuts, wrap and chill until ready to serve.

title: yams in orange sauce
directions: Peel yams and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices, discarding thin ends.
Overlapping the slices, arrange in rows in a shallow 3-quart casserole.
Set aside.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, milk and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill dough until stiff enough to roll into balls 3/4 inches in diameter.

title: scallop and fish newburg
directions: Brown bread cubes in 1/4 cup butter; set aside.
Make white sauce; mix together 1/4 cup butter, flour, milk and water.
Mix well.
Season with bouillon cube, salt, pepper and onion.
Arrange fish pieces and scallops in sea shells.
Pour white sauce over fish pieces and scallops.
Decorate each serving with olives and bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Slice potato in rounds.
Add raisins; cover with boiling water.
Cook until potatoes are slightly tender.
Place potatoes and raisins in buttered baking dish.
Place orange over potatoes. Add cinnamon, salt, juice and butter.
Cover.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sauce
directions: Mix and cook 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, salt, vanilla, butter and syrup; mix well.
Add pecans, mixing well.
Pour into shell and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add milk and water.
Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat.
Very good with fried fish.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli and drain for 45 minutes. Add soup, cheese and onion. Top with crackers.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oree's choir break dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add together.
Add oats and chips.

title: walnut clusters
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add melted chocolate, then flour, salt and baking powder.
Last, add walnuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not bake over 10 minutes.

title: one-skillet supper
directions: Brown pork chops in a large skillet over medium heat. Sprinkle rice over chops. Add all other ingredients. Cover skillet and reduce heat to low. Simmer mixture until rice has absorbed the liquid and chops are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients into slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed.
Bake at least 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix together and heat until hot.
Serve with chips.

title: creamy tomato aspic
directions: Heat soup and water.
Add cheese; stir until blended.
Add jello; whip with an egg beater. Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Fold in chopped vegetables.
Pour into a greased ring mold.
Serves 6.

title: any flavor cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, Cool Whip and egg.
This is very hard to mix.
You may have to use your hand and swish between your fingers.
Make small ball of dough and roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: irish scones
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet.
More sugar may be sprinkled on top of scones before baking.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: old cupcake
directions: Place flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, shortening and milk in bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes in cupcake pan, greased and floured or cupcake paper liners.

title: african stew with okra
directions: In a blender or food processor puree the onion, green pepper, garlic, parsley and tomatoes; set aside.
Heat the oil in a saucepan and brown the meat on all sides.
Add the tomato mixture to the meat.
If puree seems too thick, add a little water or stock.
Cover and simmer until the meat is tender and done.
Add the okra and cook for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Serves 4.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, brown sugar, water and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in eggs.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded measuring tablespoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased sheet. Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 2 to 4 minutes.

title: swiss steaks
directions: Bring beef broth to a boil in a skillet.
Add potatoes.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add beans and celery.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove vegetables and broth from skillet.
Add oil to skillet.
Brown steaks on each side.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Return vegetables and broth to pan.
Stir in mustard.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until hot.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer for around 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in potatoes, sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: tangy blue cheese dip
directions: Gradually blend soup into cream cheese.
Add Blue cheese and onion.
Chill.
Serve with chips, crackers or fresh vegetables. Also good as a topping for baked potatoes.

title: pecan squash
directions: Pierce squash in several places to allow steam to escape. Place in microwave oven.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Cut squash crosswise into halves and remove seeds.
Arrange, cut side down, on microwavable serving plate.
Cover tightly and microwave for 7 to 9 minutes or until tender.
Remove stems and cut thin slice from pointed ends to prevent tipping.

title: golden broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine broccoli, carrot, onion and water.
Cover; microwave on High for 5 minutes or until veggies are tender.
In small bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Stir in milk, cheese and pepper; mix well.
Cover; cook on High for 8 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Stir twice while cooking.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Put water, ground chuck and chopped onions in saucepan; do not brown meat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
For last hour, pot may be covered after desired consistency is reached.

title: lazy woman's pie
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a large baking dish.
Pour mixture of flour, milk, sugar and fruit in a baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
May be served warm or cold.

title: cherry crumble squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/4 cup melted margarine and eggs.
Stir until moist.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan greased on bottom only.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Combine frosting mix with margarine and sprinkle over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil in skillet until tender.
Add soups, green chilies, pimentos, chicken and Velveeta cheese.
Mix well. Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Alternate layers of tortilla squares and soup mixture in a 9 x 12-inch casserole until all ingredients are used. Top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until heated and cheese is melted. Yields 12 servings.

title: deviled crab
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Saute. Place crab meat in a large bowl.
Add sauteed foods.
Add Tabasco, pepper and Ritz crackers.
Mix with fork by tossing.
Place in shells lightly.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Note:
I used Cost Cutter chips from Kroger.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, green pepper, celery, onion and peas in a salad bowl.
Spread the mayonnaise over the layers.
Sprinkle sugar over this.
Crumble bacon over sugar.
Add Cheddar cheese. You may also toss it all.

title: italian spaghetti chicken
directions: Cook chicken in enough broth to cook other ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender.
Remove from broth and debone.
In broth, cook celery, onion and bell pepper until tender. Add to broth 1 large package of spaghetti, tomatoes, tomato juice, soup, pimento and chili powder.
When done, add chicken (about 30 minutes).
Place in a large pan.
Cover with 1/2 pound grated cheese.
Place in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and beat well.
Form walnut-size balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: egg in a basket(great kids dish)
directions: Cut a 2-inch circle in center of bread using a jelly glass or juice glass. Place bread in hot, lightly greased skillet. Break egg in center of bread; fry until done. Use the center circle of the bread to toast in skillet. Serve with jelly.

title: crock dills
directions: Place dill on bottom of crock.
Place whole cukes next.
Add pickling spice and whole garlic.
Boil water; add salt, vinegar and alum.
Cool.
Pour over cukes.
Place lid on top.
Ready in 4 days.

title: beavan's tandy takes
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add flour and vanilla.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in milk and add to the mixture.
Pour onto a greased jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Immediately after taking cake out of the oven, spread peanut butter over top.
Cool.
Melt the Hershey bars in 2 tablespoons butter and spread on top of cake.
Let cool.
Makes about 24 squares.

title: easy black beans and yellow rice(no fat)
directions: Rice:
Combine water, rice and turmeric in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: any stew
directions: Brown meat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients in a 5-quart crock-pot and cook on high for 6 to 7 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients until smooth.
Remove strings.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix together remaining 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
This may be frozen.

title: golden summer punch
directions: Add water to frozen concentrates as directed on cans and combine with pineapple juice.
Chill.
Serve in a punch bowl and garnish with orange slices.

title: easy turkey casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 of cheese.
Pour into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Top with the 1/2 cup cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook ground meat until brown.
Add cabbage into the ground meat and cook until it fries down.
Add onions, bell pepper and celery.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Add rice.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes.
Cook rice before adding to casserole.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Form into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.
Some of the unbaked sausage balls may be frozen, if desired, since recipe makes a large quantity.

title: zesty hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in an inch or so of boiling, salted water until just tender.
Slice or dice the potatoes without peeling; set aside.

title: tasty cheese bread
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on halved French bread loaves.
One loaf of this bread has about 20 pieces.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° to melt cheese. To freeze, cover with Saran Wrap and then foil.
It is easy to double this recipe and it is great as an appetizer or as a side to your favorite soup or salad.

title: meatballs with rice and gravy
directions: Mix well and roll into small balls. Brown. In a saucepan, add 2 cans cream of mushroom soup and 1 can water, then add meatballs. Simmer for 20 minutes. Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or noodles (rice is the best).

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion on medium heat. Break apart. Drain. Stir in salsa. Continue to heat to boiling point. Lower heat. Add cheese. Stir until melted. Do not allow salsa to boil. Serve with chips.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix and form into meatballs.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Drain.

title: zucchini-sausage skillet
directions: Crumble sausage in large skillet and saute along with onion until lightly browned.
Slice squash 1/4 inch
thick over browned sausage.
Sprinkle with salt, oregano and garlic powder.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Slice cream cheese over zucchini.
Return cover until cheese is melted.
Gently fold mixture until cream cheese is evenly distributed.
Serve hot.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Combine oil, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and sesame seed.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over broccoli.
Coat all spears.
Refrigerate.
Delicious!

title: sausage rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper until soft.
Add sausage until browned and crumbly. Add mushrooms, garlic and spices.
Cook about 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in rice.
Add stock.
Boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook until liquid is absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: andy's potato doughnuts
directions: Beat mashed potatoes and add melted shortening, beaten eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, salt, nutmeg and baking powder. Add potato mixture.
Dough should be soft, yet firm enough to roll.
Separate in two parts and roll to 3/4-inch thickness. Cut with doughnut cutter and cook in deep fat at 365°.
Fry until golden brown and drain on absorbent paper.
Dust with powdered sugar or a cinnamon sugar mixture.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix well, then add 9 cups of oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat, remove and drain.
Saute onions and garlic in 3 tablespoons oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, pepper, Italian herbs, sugar and meat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine eggs, spinach, Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Layers: lasagne noodles, cheese mixture, meat mixture and Mozzarella.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mushrooms a la greque
directions: In large skillet, bring to boil broth, wine, oil, juice, salt, garlic and thyme.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Place mushrooms in marinade; cover and simmer 4 minutes or until only slightly cooked.
Remove with a slotted spoon; set aside. Cook carrot in marinade 3 minutes.
Remove.
Add green pepper and cook one minute.
Mix vegetables and divide between 2 hot sterilized 1 pint jars.
Pour in enough marinade to cover.
Close tight.
Refrigerate up to 3 weeks.

title: butter rolls
directions: Make biscuit dough with 2 cups flour.
Roll out to 1/4-inch or 1/8-inch thickness on floured board.
Cover with 1 cup softened butter; spread out.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar.
Sprinkle liberally with vanilla flavoring all over top.
Roll lengthwise into roll (as for cinnamon rolls).
Cut about 1/2-inch thick. Place coiled side up (makes a broiler pan full).
Pour milk over top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over top.
Dot with 8 slices butter. Sprinkle with vanilla flavoring again.
Cook on top of stove until begins to bubble.
Put in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Watch closely or will boil over. Brown under broiler.

title: applesauce delight
directions: Whip Dream Whip as directed on package and add softened cream cheese.
Then add marshmallows.
Let stand in refrigerator until needed.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix jello and 9 cups boiling water; set aside to cool.
Bring to a boil 4 cups sugar and 4 cups water.
Combine with jello and set aside to cool.
Add lemon juice, pineapple juice and crushed pineapple.
Freeze in covered container. Remove from freezer about 4 to 4 1/2 hours prior to serving.
Do not thaw completely.
Add ginger ale slowly to mix.
Serve slushy.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Lightly grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender (high) or 1 minute with hand beater. Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed peppers ala mike
directions: Cut off top of peppers and clean out the seeds and seed ribs. In a bowl mix the chopped meat, rice, eggs, sage, water, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
The mixture should be soft.
If it isn't, add a little more water.
Fill the pepper cavities with the mixture and bake in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: whipped shortbread
directions: Using a heavy-duty mixer, beat butter on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Gradually add dry ingredients, beating constantly, until well blended.

title: fat-free ranch roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on flour tortilla. Roll up, chill and slice into pinwheels.

title: hot water chestnuts or scallops
directions: Roll bacon strips around water chestnuts (or scallops). Secure with toothpicks.
Place under broiler until bacon is crisp.
Serve hot.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift flour and mix dry ingredients together.
Mix oil, orange rind, orange juice and eggs together.
Combine dry and liquid ingredients together. Stir in cranberries until well blended. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Turn out and cool completely.

title: hawaiian dream cake(bake 1 week in advance; refrigerate covered.)
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat together thoroughly.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add carrot, coconut mixture and blend.
Bake in a large square or rectangular pan at 350° for 1 hour or until center is firm.
After the week curing period, serve with whipped cream or rum butter as for fruit cake.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash, core and slice apples (do not peel).
Place them in a heavy skillet in which the butter or drippings have been melted. Cover and cook over moderate heat until soft (5 to 10 minutes), then uncover and sprinkle with sugar.
Cook, uncovered, until apples are delicately browned on underside.
If overcooked, the apples will fall to pieces.
Serve hot.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Cream shortening and flour.
Add margarine and 7-Up.
Put into bowl and seal.
Shake until mixture forms a soft ball.

title: long john batter
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add egg yolk and water and mix until smooth.
Add beaten egg white.
May be used to dip fish, chicken fillets or onion rings.
Fry in hot oil.

title: french strawberry glace pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Simmer 1 cup strawberries and 2/3 cup water about 3 minutes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and remaining 1/3 cup water.
Add to boiling mixture. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Spread cream cheese over bottom of cooled, baked pie shell.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Slice cauliflower and olives 1/8-inch thick, dice green peppers 1/4 inch.
Mix sour cream, salad dressing, Italian dressing seasoning mix, garlic, dill weed and vinegar in bowl. Add cauliflower, olives and peppers.
Let stand one hour before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: poppy seed bread(so easy! so good!)
directions: Combine
ingredients and beat.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: beef stew in cream sauce with turnips(low-carb)
directions: Brown beef in grape seed oil on high in large Dutch oven pan. Sprinkle seasonings on beef. Add turnip chunks. Add water. Cover pan. Reduce temperature to low simmer. Cook 2 hours. When there is about 20 minutes left, melt butter in saucepan and saute mushrooms and onions until tender.
Add to beef mixture. Add cream and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer whole pot until 2 hours total are up.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine vegetables and chicken broth. Cook vegetables until tender, about 15 minutes.
Combine milk, flour and seasonings and stir into the chicken broth mixture. Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly.
Stir in cheese. Cook until melted.
Add jalapenos if desired.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into cakes.
Broil or fry in oil.

title: aunt dolly morris' nine egg cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and flour.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: uncle johnny's enchiladas
directions: Mix enchilada sauce and water in shallow skillet.
Heat to medium warm.
Mix chilies and cheese in container.
Dip each tortilla in enchilada sauce leaving excess sauce in pan.
Place tortilla on plate and put
1 Tbsp. chili and small amount of cheese down the middle.
Roll up and place in a 9x13 baking pan. Continue dipping, filling and rolling until pan is full and packed together.
Mix remaining enchilada sauce with chili.
Pour over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese, covering enchiladas.
Cover with aluminium foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with corn chips, hot peppers and salsa.

title: mom's cherry cake
directions: Pour pie filling and pineapple in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of that.
Pour margarine on top of dry cake mix.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry crepes
directions: Beat eggs until blended.
Add milk and vanilla; blend until smooth.
Add flour slowly, blending until smooth.
Batter should have consistency of heavy cream.
Add about 1 tablespoon oil to 8-inch frypan and coat bottom.
(Do not use nonstick pans.)
Heat over medium heat until just starting to smoke.
Add about 2 tablespoons batter, lift and tilt pan to spread batter evenly. Cook quickly, then flip crepe to cook second side.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook the carrots until just tender.
Combine with all ingredients.
Marinate 12 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: hot chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine soup, broth, tomatoes and celery; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and add cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Add chopped pieces of chicken.
Pour mixture over noodles in baking dish and mix well.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: salmon in a blanket
directions: Combine 2
cups Bisquick and 2/3 cup milk to make dough and roll
in oblong shape, 7 x 15-inches.
Transfer to lightly greased baking
sheet.
Mix rest of ingredients and place down the center of dough to within 2-inches of ends.
Fold lengthwise edge
of dough
over salmon mixture to overlap.
Fold in ends and roll over so seam is underneath.
Make slashes on top for steam
to
escape. Bake
at
for
12 to 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in large baking dish, skin side up.
Mix cheese and soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Dip cookies in milk and line bottom of pie plate.
Spread half of Cool Whip on top of cookies.
Put another layer of cookies on top of Cool Whip, then put the last of the Cool Whip on.
You can sprinkle crumbled cookies on top, if desired.
Chill in refrigerator or freeze until ready to serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Put broccoli, carrots and mushrooms in large bowl.
Sprinkle with vinegar and dash of Parmesan cheese.
Let set about 10 minutes.
Add chicken and mix.
Add twist macaroni, pour on dressing and mix.

title: greek mushroom salad
directions: Mix first 3 items and, before serving, toss with last 4 items.

title: mexican meat cups
directions: Roll or pat each biscuit to a 3 1/2 to 4-inch circle; fit over backs of well-greased muffin pans.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 9 minutes.
Brown meat; drain off fat.
Stir in beans, sandwich sauce and water.
Heat to boiling.
With a metal spatula, remove biscuits from pans.
Fill with meat sauce.
Top with cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Makes 10.

title: daphne's corn fritters
directions: Mix and fry in hot grease.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook macaroni and drain. Cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, then tomatoes. Cook until thickened.
Add cheese. Stir until melted. Stir in seasoning.
Combine sauce and macaroni in casserole. Bake 20 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix persimmon pulp, beaten eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and pour liquid mixture into them.
Stir in melted margarine.
Pour into shallow, oiled pan to depth of about 2 inches.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
This is good cold or hot.

title: airways sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks till thick and fluffy.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Sift flour and salt together and add alternately with water.
Add lemon rind.
Beat egg whites till foamy, add baking powder and beat till they hold a peak.
Fold into yolk mixture. Pour into ungreased angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 - 60 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a sauce pan stir first 4 ingredients.
Boil on medium heat about 5 minutes.
Take off heat.
Stir in peanut butter (crunchy is good).
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir.
Add oatmeal.
Stop adding if unable to stir.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 5 minutes, then beat 1 minute on High.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans 45 minutes at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: Beat 3/4 cup sugar, flour, milk, butter, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Beat well.
Pour in greased pan.
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa and put on top of cake mixture, then pour 1 1/2 cups water over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine, pecans, 1/4 cup sugar.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1 cup sugar; put on top of pecan mixture.
Mix Jell-O, boiling water and strawberries.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture to make the third layer.
Chill.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Rinse with hot water and drain.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish (large).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs(main dish)
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup.
Make 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs; drain grease.
Pour soup in skillet with meatballs. Simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve with noodles (I like orzo) or rice.

title: mexican dish or dip
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain and add rest of ingredients. Stir and heat well.
Eat with plain Doritos.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Combine sugar, milk and
corn syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate bits.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and let this stand overnight.
The following day, toss all ingredients together before serving.

title: liniment
directions: Nail polish will last longer if you add 2 teaspoonfuls of vinegar to 2 1/2 cups lukewarm water, then dip finger tips into this solution for a few seconds before applying polish.

title: simple carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill thoroughly.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, combine apples, sweetened condensed milk and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, cut 1/2 cup of margarine into 1 cup biscuit mix until crumbly.
Stir in apple mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together except cheese.
Put in lightly greased casserole and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Combine sugar and butter; beat well.
Add eggs and beat again. Stir in chocolate, flour and salt, mix until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts; pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
The secret is to not overcook.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Stir together flour and baking powder; set aside.
Beat butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and almond extract; mix well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: peach strudel
directions: Slice peaches and mix with 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and egg together.
(This will be a crumbly mixture.) Sprinkle evenly over peaches.
Pour melted butter over the crumb mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ham loaves
directions: Combine eggs, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend in ham and pork.
Mix in bread crumbs.
Shape into loaves.
Place in an ungreased baking dish, filled with 1/2-inch of cold water. Combine brown sugar and pineapple juice from rings.
Baste loaves and decorate with pineapple rings.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Yields 2 large loaves or 6 small loaves.

title: mr. kenney's chili
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add the chili powder and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add stewed tomatoes and cook 5 to 10 more minutes.
Cook down and stir, adding the Ranch Style beans.
Cook until done.

title: icebox tea rolls
directions: Mix together.
Beat up.
Let raise for 2 hours.
Thicken with more flour.
Let raise until light.
Work out in rolls.
Let rise until double.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown.

title: spanish bread
directions: Mix together ingredients, except for cheese.
Pour half of mixture in baking dish.
Put grated cheese on top of mixture.
Add rest of mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over oleo. Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into cubes. Coat with flour, salt and pepper. Brown in oil. Add onion and juice from tomatoes (reserving tomatoes). Add Kitchen Bouquet and water. Simmer 50 to 60 minutes. Add bell pepper, cut in 1-inch pieces. Add Worcestershire sauce. Cook 10 minutes. Add tomatoes. Cook 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large casserole.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook Uncle Ben's long grain rice.
Bake chicken breasts for 30 minutes at 350°.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms.
Put half the rice mix, mixed with the onion, celery and mushrooms, in a greased casserole.
Add undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Arrange cooked chicken on top of this and cover with the rest of rice mixture. Take 1/2 bag of bread crumbs mixed with 1/4 cup of melted butter and put around the edges of the casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: bean and cabbage soup(low-fat)
directions: Bring broth, water, cabbage, carrots, onion and allspice to a boil in a large pot.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 12 minutes, until vegetables are firm-tender.
Add beans and dill; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients.
Pour into well greased 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until set, except middle will still shake a little.

title: irish coffee pudding
directions: Mix gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and coffee in the top of a double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and water together.
Add gelatin mixture.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in remaining sugar.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Top with whipped cream, when chilled.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients all together in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Press in sides and bottom.
Refrigerate to chill.

title: corn flake dream bars
directions: Cream 1/2 cup brown sugar. Add butter and flour. Pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into loaf.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Half hour before it's finished, add remaining tomato soup to top of loaf.

title: holiday broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Saute celery and onion until tender.
Heat soup and cheese together until cheese melts.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and place in a 350° oven.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until bread crumbs are browned. Delicious!

title: walnut raisin cookies
directions: In one bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda.
In second bowl, combine softened butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Slowly add flour mixture.
Batter should be stiff.
Mix in chopped walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: "lee and erkinger's favorite potato dish"(or cheesy potatoes)
directions: Boil the potatoes with a bay leaf 35 to 40 minutes, until tender.
Let cool.
Peel and dice the potatoes.
Melt together cream of chicken soup and butter.
Add green onions, 1 1/2 cups cheese, sour cream and salt and pepper.
Pour over the potatoes and stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cheese to top and bake again until melted.

title: corn chowder
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add potatoes, onion, garlic and celery. Return water to boil and add bouillon and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove 2 cups potatoes from stock and set aside.
Blend remaining chowder. Reheat over low heat.
Add corn and reserve potatoes.
Simmer, stirring for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in small skillet.
Add green pepper and scallions.
Saute approximately 3 minutes.
Stir into chowder.

title: scotch 'n chocolate pie
directions: In 4-cup measure, place pudding mix; add brown sugar.
Blend in milk gradually until smooth.
Microwave on High until mixture thickens (5 to 6 minutes, stirring twice during cooking).
Remove 1/2 pudding; add chocolate and stir until melted.
Pour into baked pie crust.
To remaining pudding, add margarine and vanilla.
Cook at lukewarm and pour over chocolate layer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with whipped topping and garnish with shaved chocolate, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and crumble ground beef.
Drain well.
Add 1 package taco seasoning mix; combine well.
Add salsa.
Let cool.
Spread refried beans in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cooled beef mixture.
Add 1 package taco seasoning mix to sour cream; mix well until smooth.
Spread on top of meat mixture.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes and onions over sour cream.
Top with shredded cheese and olives.
Chill before serving.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: On an ovenproof platter or baking dish, layer the following: turkey, dressing, gravy, mushrooms, onions.
Top off with grated cheese and bake in oven until heated thoroughly and cheese has melted.

title: "almost better than sex" cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
When cake is done, poke holes on top with straw.
Cook the sugar and crushed pineapple.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cake.
Let the cake cool!!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add oil and sugar and beat really well.
Add vanilla, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and flour; beat 2 minutes.
Add nuts and zucchini and pour into loaf pans. Make 2 big loaves or 3 little ones.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for big loaves and 45 minutes for small ones.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup.
Add bacon drippings, salt and pepper. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Place bacon strips and onion on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce and sweet peppers in large bowl.
Cut tops of sweet peppers and clean inside.
Stuff with meat mix.
Place in medium to large pot.
Pour tomato sauce in.
Add some water (1/2 cup).
Put ketchup on tops.
Cover pot. Cook on medium heat for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve over rice or with vegetables and potatoes.
Mmm!

title: butternut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until light and foamy in a large bowl.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended. Stir in nuts (mixture will be stiff).
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes, then cut into bars.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on; slice.
Melt oleo in bottom of casserole.
Add sliced potatoes, bread cubes and onion.
Melt cheese and pour over all.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes mixed with melted oleo over top.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Before ready to bake, pour milk over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bean sprout and pepper salad
directions: Mix soy sauce, vinegar and vegetable and sesame oils in small bowl.
Set aside.
Rinse bean sprouts under cold running water. Drain.
Cut carrots into 1-inch lengths; cut lengthwise into 1/16-inch thick slices.
Stack the slices and cut lengthwise into 1/8-inch wide strips.
Cut green peppers lengthwise into quarters; cut quarters lengthwise into 1/8-inch wide strips.
(Note:
You don't need to be fussy.
You just need skinny strips of carrot and pepper!)

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine
all
ingredients and spoon into
a buttered 6-cup casserole.
Dot the top with the rest
of the butter.
Bake, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
(You can add chopped pimento or brown an onion in butter and add.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass cake pan, layer crushed pretzels and oleo.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
When crust is cool, prepare second layer.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar. Mix well and spread on first layer.
Dissolve Jell-O in water as directed.
When partially congealed in separate bowl, add frozen strawberries that have been thawed.
Spread this mixture on second layer.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute carrots, celery and onion in margarine until tender, but do not brown.
Stir in chicken broth. Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in butter then roll in mixture of potato chips, garlic salt and pepper.
Place pieces skin side up, not touching, in shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Do not turn.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt butter, marshmallows and milk over low heat.
Add crushed vanilla wafers and cook until melted.
Chop fruit and nuts and mix with coconut.
Fold fruit and nuts into batter.
Shape into a cake and freeze.
Will keep in the refrigerator for several days.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans, onion, salt and green pepper. Shape into a ball.
Roll ball in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic or foil and refrigerate until well chilled (overnight).

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar, flour and butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie crust and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Warm oil in 10-inch skillet.
Over medium-low heat, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover pan and cook 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve immediately.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Flake salmon and remove bones.
Beat egg and add to salmon. Stir soda into milk and add to all other ingredients except oil. Drop teaspoons of mixture into deep hot hooking oil.
Cook until brown.

title: hot buttered apple drink
directions: Beat butter, brown sugar and spices until light and fluffy. Cover.
Store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: hot dog it's macaroni
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite-size pieces.
Tear cheese into small pieces.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Stir in the hot dogs, cheese, vegetables and milk.
Heat over medium heat.
Cook and stir 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes, then add soda.
Pour over popped corn that is in a large pan.
Mix so that all the corn is covered.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: tomato basil sauce
directions: Whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour
over
tomatoes and 1/2 basil.
Let stand 1 to 4 hours
at
room temperature.
Before serving, add last half of basil.
Serve with or over rice.
Crusty rolls are good to dip in the juice and green beans compliment it.

title: carrot pineapple salad
directions: Completely dissolve jello in the 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Combine 1 cup water and ice cubes to make 2 1/2 cups water and ice.
Add to jello with the 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Stir for 2 minutes.
Let stand until slightly thickened.
Fold in pineapple and carrots.
Chill.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix all ingredients (except jello) and cook until rhubarb is done.
Take off heat.
Then add strawberry jello and pour into containers.
Let set overnight.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt together the oleo, marshmallows and jello.
Pour over popcorn and shape into balls.
You may use different flavors of jello.
Pick the color to match the holiday!

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, then add lemon flavoring.
Mix well.
Add flour and 7-up.
Beat with electric mixer at least 5 minutes.
bake in tube or bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place hash browns in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(No need to thaw potatoes.)
Break potatoes apart and mix in cheese cubes. Mix other ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Bake in 325° oven if using glass dish for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pour popped corn in the brown bag that has the other bag inside (double bagged).
Put margarine, Karo syrup, salt and brown sugar in a cooking pot and cook at medium heat until it boils for 1 minute.
Remove from the flame and add vanilla and then soda. Stir (it will foam), then pour over popped corn in the bag.
Shake very well.
Roll the bag top over the popcorn and put into the microwave for 1 1/2 minutes at High heat.
Shake after removed and put back in for 40 seconds.
Remove again and pour into a cookie sheet.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: pigs in a blanket(cabbage rolls)
directions: Cut around cabbage core.
Put in large pot, cover with water, and bring to a boil.
The leaves will come off.
Mix ground beef, chopped onion, rice, ground sausage, 4 Tbsp. tomatoes and mix well. Remove cabbage leaves and cut out stems.
Put two Tbsp. mixture on leaves and roll loosely.
Place sauerkraut and dill seed in bottom of large kettle.
Add green stuffed pepper in middle with cabbage rolls around.
Add remaining tomatoes with 3 cups water. Cover and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Serve with sour cream.

title: carol's no-fat refried beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in refrigerator.
Serve 1/2 cup of this mixture over 1 corn tortilla. Cook 3 egg whites and serve over tortillas and beans.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons fat-free sour cream.

title: mound candy
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat and add milk and vanilla.
Mix sugar, dry milk and coconut.
Mix well. Shape into balls and cool.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Mix everything and pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and garnish with cherries.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover pan and remove from heat.
Raisins can be added, if desired.
In large bowl put Marshmallow Creme or marshmallows.
Add pineapple.
After the rice has stood for 5 minutes, pour over the marshmallows and pineapple.
Let it sit for 10 minutes, then stir well.
Nutmeg can be sprinkled over the top or mixed through.
Let cool well. Whipped cream may be added before serving.
This makes a large bowl full.

title: diane's yeast rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Measure water in separate bowl. Add yeast and 1/2 teaspoon of flour mixture to water.
Stir and set aside.
Cut shortening into the remaining flour mixture.
Add water mixture.
Mix. Dump onto floured board and knead.
Let rise.
Knead again.
Pinch off and shape into rolls.
Brush with melted butter. Let rise.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna 12 minutes. Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; form balls.
Chill.
Very slowly melt semi-sweet baking chocolate.
Dip frozen peanut butter balls into chocolate.
Let cool on wax paper.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, catsup and garlic. Press biscuits (20) into well-greased muffin cups.
Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons meat into each biscuit.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the crushed pretzels, melted margarine and 4 tablespoons of sugar together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir in soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, chestnuts and onions.
Cover; chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain grease from hamburger. Add all ingredients and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Mix puree, salt, water and bay leaves together in 1 1/2 to 2-quart saucepan. Bring to slow boil and simmer 15 minutes. Dig out bay leaves and discard; add lemon Jell-O to hot mixture and mix thoroughly to dissolve completely. Add vinegar. Pour aspic into a flat container so it will chill more quickly; when slightly jelled, fold in minced onion. You may leave the aspic in the container or pour into individual molds and allow to set completely. Serve on lettuce leaf or your choice.

title: grilled hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pat out hamburgers to desired thickness and grill to desired doneness.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in the oil until soft.
Add ground beef and seasonings, stirring until meat loses its pink color.
Stir in the cooked rice, the tomatoes and the Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream pie
directions: In large pan, slightly beat egg yolks and 2 egg whites.
Add sugar, sour cream, raisins, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked shells and cover with meringue.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses and mix together.
Add bits, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Form into ball and roll in pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine the two sugars.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bits and scotch bits over hot, but not boiling water.
Blend well.
Pour evenly over Rice Krispies mixture.
Cool until firm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat milk, cream cheese and peanut butter together until smooth. Stir in container of Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker or chocolate pie crust. Garnish with chocolate syrup.

title: italian peas
directions: Cook the onion in the bacon grease in a medium skillet until clear.
Add the peas and tomatoes.
Season to taste.
Cook approximately 5 minutes over medium heat.

title: cowboy cookies(mr. hendrickson's favorite)
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Add the last 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Put in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch dip
directions: Pour sour cream into small mixing bowl.
Add party dip mix. Stir and chill for 5-10 minutes.

title: shake 'em up bars
directions: Drop 2 eggs into a quart jar with screw top.
Add sugar, oil and wine.
Screw on top and shake 20 times or until well blended. Add salt, flour and baking powder.
Screw on top and shake 40 times.
Pour into greased 8 x 10-inch or 7 x 11-inch pan.
Ground walnuts can be sprinkled on top of batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fudge nougat - candy
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk and bring to a boil in saucepan.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in remaining ingredients and spread mixture into buttered 12 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and boil for 1 minute.
Makes enough for 10 chicken halves and can be stored in refrigerator.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Put all ingredients, except nuts, in large mixer bowl and beat on medium speed (number 6 or 7) until well blended and the batter is smooth.
Grease a 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan with pancoat.
Pour batter in pan and sprinkle nuts over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test cake for doneness before removing from oven.
Remove from oven and while cake is still hot, stick over entire top of cake with a fork.
While cake is still hot, drizzle glaze over the entire top.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Cook peaches, sugar and 1 stick oleo until tender.
Add extract.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo in baking dish.
Then mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour over peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: crunch peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl combine the peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Add cereal and stir until until well coated. In small microwave safe bowl combine chocolate chips and shortening. Microwave uncovered for 1-2 minutes or until chips are melted. Stir until smooth. Roll cereal mixture into tiny balls. Dip in chocolate. Place on a wax paper lined pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: kansas corn scallop
directions: Drain liquid from whole corn into a cup. Beat eggs slightly in large bowl; stir in corn plus 1/4 cup corn liquid. Add cream-style corn, evaporated milk, melted butter, onion, salt and pepper. Fold in crackers and diced cheese. Spoon into greased 8-cup baking dish. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour or until set. Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate delite
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Saute spinach in butter.
Add onion, cottage cheese, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix.
Add cheese.
Place in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until firm.

title: hidden valley ranch herb cheese
directions: Use electric mixer to blend all ingredients.
Store in large crock.
Can be refrigerated a couple of weeks.
Serve with crackers.

title: under the sea salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water. Add pear juice, salt and vinegar. Pour half of this mixture into an 8-inch jello mold. Chill until firm. Chill remaining jello until cold and syrupy. Put the syrupy jello in a bowl and whip until frothy. Have cream cheese at room temperature; cream together with ginger. Fold into whipped jello gradually.
Fold in the pears. Pour over first half of chilled jello which should be well set by now. Chill.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut and sugar and let stand 1/2 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients with sauerkraut and sugar.
Refrigerate about 12 hours.
Stir through occasionally.

title: four bean bake
directions: Cook kielbasa and cut in chunks or small pieces.
Simmer onion, then add ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Mix all ingredients together.
(A crock-pot can be used.)

title: delicious wheat-free pancakes
directions: Stir together cornmeal, flour, baking soda, sugar or honey and salt. Add buttermilk or yogurt, oil and egg yolk.
Blend well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in. Let batter stand for 10 minutes. Bake on hot griddle, turning once.
Makes about 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: fruit bar cookies
directions: Mix together and boil five minutes the sugar, raisins, shortening and hot water.
Then add spices and mix well.
Allow to cool to lukewarm.
Then add the beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cooled mixture.
Stir well.
Add dates and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost and cut into squares.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Add sugar, salt and spices to mixture.
Stir in milk.
Add molasses and blend.
Pour into crusts and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt with milk; stir constantly.
Cool on low heat until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and coconut.
Cool, then pour into a pie shell.

title: tuna fish salad plate
directions: Drain off all water from tuna.
Separate and mash tuna with a fork.
Mix all ingredients.
Add small amount of Miracle Whip at a time, just enough to hold mixture together.
Chill in refrigerator. Place chilled lettuce leaves on plates.
Add tuna salad (a nice size serving) in middle of lettuce.
Arrange sliced fresh orange, pear halves, tomato wedges, sliced avocado and few ripe olives to garnish.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix sausage, bread crumbs, peppers, mushrooms and onion.
Put in loaf pan.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over sausage mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top and refrigerate a couple of hours.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pam's chicken breasts
directions: Spray bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place the dried beef over (coating) the bottom of the pan.
Place the chicken on top of the dried beef.
Mix the sour cream and soup together; pour over the chicken breasts.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 325°; remove foil and bake for another hour.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order in large bowl and chill for 24 hours.
Mix and serve.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Work dough.
Pinch and roll 2-inch ball.
Stand 5 minutes on board.
Roll flat with rolling pin.
Prick with fork.
Fry in hot deep shortening.
Cook quickly for 5 seconds.
Turn once and cook 5 seconds on other side.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: In large bowl, mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter until crumbly. Press on bottom of sheet cake pan. In another bowl, add cream cheese and gradually add sweetened condensed milk and 2 eggs. Add pumpkin pie mix. Pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: freeze-ahead peach pie filling
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour into four 9-inch foil pie pans.
Place in freezer until frozen solid.
Wrap tightly or place in large Ziploc bag. Keep frozen until ready to use.
To bake, remove from pan and place in an unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust and seal. Bake at 400° for 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grilled catfish
directions: Wash fillets and remove any skin, fins or imperfections.
Pat dry.
Season liberally with Cajun seasoning.
Place in shallow dish.
Mix approximately equal amounts of soy sauce, oil and wine (plus any other desired flavors).
Make enough to cover the fillets about halfway up.
Pour over fillets.
Turn after 10 minutes.
Let marinate about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Boil first four ingredients to soft ball stage.
Cool.
Add butter, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Beat. Pour into buttered pan.

title: herbed tenderloin
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine seasoning ingredients; press evenly into roast.
Place on rack in a shallow pan.
Roast approximately 45 to 50 minutes for medium rare to medium doneness. Remove roast when meat thermometer registers 140° for medium-rare or 155° for medium.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 15 minutes. Slice and season with salt.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: ruth's chess pie
directions: Sift meal and sugar together.
Melt butter and remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add cornmeal, sugar, vinegar, lightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: amish zucchini casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef in a skillet; drain off all drippings and place in a casserole dish.
Put zucchini over meat.
Peel tomatoes, quarter, shave out most of seeds, then slice to cover zucchini layer.
Top with diced onions.
Add a layer of Velveeta.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: savory chopped spinach
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook spinach according to package directions; drain well and return to saucepan.
Add cream cheese and stir until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well combined.
Put mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Set casserole in a preheated 350° oven and bake until mixture is hot throughout, 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mini cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl, combine biscuit mix, cheese and garlic.
With a fork, stir in milk just until moistened.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine butter and garlic powder; brush over biscuits.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: tortellini pesto soup
directions: Combine green onion and chicken broth in 5-quart saucepan. Bring to boiling over high heat. Gradually stir the tortellini into the broth.
Reduce the heat to medium-high.
Cook 3 minutes. Gradually stir in the pea pods.
Continue cooking for another 3 minutes.
Stir in pesto sauce. Serve.

title: bruce's one pot college dinner
directions: Slice hot dogs.
Boil water for macaroni, put hot dogs and macaroni in boiling water.
Cook until macaroni is done.
Drain. Return to pot.
Pour in soup, chili and cheese from package. Stir.
Heat until warm.
If mixture looks thick, add a little more water.
(I assume that since he had only one pot, the water from the macaroni was not totally drained.)
Divide between 4 dishes. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top if you want.
Served with a salad it makes a quick, tasty meal.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta, drain and rinse well with cold water.
In a large bowl, mix the next four ingredients.
Dice and add the remaining ingredients.
Add the tomato after mixing in other ingredients. Toss in pasta and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Make the day before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and one melted stick of the butter.
Spread crust into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press flat. Beat the remaining 2 sticks of softened, not melted, margarine, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs at high speed for 2 to 5 minutes. Spread the egg mixture over the crumbs.
Layer the sliced bananas over the egg mixture.
Spread the pineapple over the bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Let chill 24 hours.
Enjoy!

title: boston cream cake
directions: Soften butter and add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add 2 egg yolks, salt, baking powder and vanilla and beat.
Use enough milk with flour for consistency.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Bake in 2 cake pans (buttered and floured) for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the pudding mix.
Sprinkle it on last and blend thoroughly.
Chill.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Mix and bring to a boil the next 5 ingredients.
Combine with beans.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°, uncovered, or can be put in crock-pot.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with dry Italian salad dressing mix. Set aside. Cut bread into small circles.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each circle. Top with a slice of cucumber. Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with fresh parsley (optional).

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° until done or springs back to touch.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt together butter and peanut butter.
Sift powdered sugar over Rice Krispies; mix.
Add melted mixture to powdered sugar mixture.
Mix well; make into balls, then stick a toothpick into each ball.
Freeze overnight.
Melt together chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip frozen balls into chocolate.
Remove toothpicks and serve.
Yummy!

title: linguine
directions: In skillet, brown garlic in 1/4 cup of oil.
Add clams and one clam can of water.
Add parsley, salt and pepper and bring to a boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Cook linguine according to package directions.
Drain.
Serve clam sauce over linguine.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown steak in oil.
Add soy sauce, broth and mushrooms. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add celery, onions and water chestnuts.
Cook 20 minutes and add bean sprouts.
Bring to a boil.
Mix water and cornstarch together.
Stir into mixture and cook until thickened. Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all above ingredients in a mixing bowl, press into hamburger patties and place in a baking pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain grease, then smother them with gravy of your choice.
Bake again for 15 minutes.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix 1/2 cup melted butter and graham crackers.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs until light.
Add powdered sugar, softened butter and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes and spread on crumbs.
Chill 30 minutes.
Put on pineapple and bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll in pecans.

title: fish with spinach (baked)(armenian)
directions: Saute chopped onion in oil.
Wash and cut haddock.
Dry on paper towels.
In plastic bag, put flour, paprika and garlic salt. Place fish in bag and shake until fish is well coated.
Wash and drain spinach.
Place in roasting pan and add 1 teaspoon salt. Put onion on the spinach, then arrange fish on top.
Add hot water and juice of lemon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade dog bones number 1
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into dog bones (you can use bone shaped cookie cutter).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 48 bones.

title: rice-artichoke salad
directions: Add juice from artichokes with 1/2 teaspoon curry powder and 1/3 cup mayo; toss all together.
Make 24 hours before serving. Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.
Delicious.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and well-beaten egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients (salt, flour and baking powder) and add gradually.
Stir in peanuts.
Place on buttered cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake in moderate oven for 8 minutes.

title: microwave butter toffee
directions: Rim the top of an 8-cup measuring bowl with the stick of butter.
Place the remaining butter in the bottom of the bowl. Add sugar, salt and water and microwave for 7 to 8 minutes.
Do not stir.
Continue adding 30 second cook times until the mixture is a light golden brown in color, about 3 minutes.
While the candy is cooking, line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil and spread the chopped nuts evenly on the foil.
When the candy is done, pour the mixture over the chopped nuts.
Do not scrape the excess syrup out of the measuring bowl.
When pouring the candy syrup on the foil and nuts, make sure to allow the candy to flow around all the nuts.
Let stand until candy is firm and cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute the five ingredients after the chicken.
Mix together the soups and salsa.
Layer the ingredients; spaghetti, chicken and sauce.	Top with 10 oz. pkg. of shredded Longhorn cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and cocoa in greased 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Add evaporated milk and butter; do not mix. Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir until mixed.
Add vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Spread evenly in dish.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24 ounces.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add soup, rice and mushrooms and cook in covered casserole for 45 minutes at 350°. This amount serves 4; can be doubled.
Mushroom liquid can be saved to reheat rice in if any left over.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Saute eggplant and zucchini in some oil until tender (7 to 8 minutes).
Transfer to large Dutch oven.
Saute onions, garlic and peppers until tender (10 minutes).
Transfer to the Dutch oven. Add both types of tomatoes, spices and parsley.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add kidney beans and peas; cook another 15 minutes.
Stir and adjust seasonings.
Garnish with sour cream and/or grated Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
Sift the flour and salt into a small bowl and set aside.
In a medium-size saucepan boil the water and butter.
Reduce the heat to low and add the flour all at once.
Stir vigorously with a wooden spoon and cook and stir until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool about 3 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth after each addition.
Drop mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls onto the cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Turn off the oven.
Slit or slice the top off each cream puff and return to the oven for about 3 minutes to dry the inside.

title: beef 'n noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, saute onions and green pepper in margarine 3 minutes or until tender.
Add beef and cook until no longer pink. Drain excess fat.

title: eggnog salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; save juice.
Soften gelatin in juice. Melt over hot water.
Combine all ingredients, pour into mold or bowl and chill.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook in crock-pot 4 to 5 hours until thick.
Stir often.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham on rack in large shallow roasting pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Trim off skin and excess fat.
Mix preserves, mustard and wine in small saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring often.
Brush ham with glaze.
Continue baking, brushing with glaze 1 hour or until richly glazed.

title: chicken artichoke dip
directions: Mix artichokes, chicken and mayonnaise together.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger pie with cheese crust
directions: Cook onion, celery, green pepper, hamburger, chili powder, 2 teaspoons salt and pepper in oil.
Add tomato soup and garlic. Put in casserole.

title: salsa (hot sauce)
directions: Simmer at least 2 hours.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Place pizza sauce on muffins and put on a baking sheet.
Set oven at 350°.
Add cheese and topping to muffins.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Take off pan and cool before eating.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: curried chicken with artichokes
directions: Mix lemon juice, cheese, curry and mayonnaise.
Mix soup, sour cream and artichokes (cut in bite size pieces) together.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with croutons (enough to cover bottom of pan).
You can use cubed, seasoned stuffing.
Place cooked chicken (cut in pieces) on top of croutons.
Pour sour cream and cheese mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Brown in 1/4 cup hot fat or vegetable oil.
Remove meat balls and make gravy.
Return meat balls to gravy; cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Add to yeast mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use as desired.
Drop spoonful in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: goulash
directions: Cook beef until tender at 350° in oven.
Tear into small pieces.
Add a little cornstarch to thicken broth just slightly. Add vegetables and cook until done.
The amount of vegetables can be changed to adjust to the amount of meat used.

title: pork chops in onion sauce(servings: 4)
directions: *Onions are to be thinly sliced.

title: easy bunny cake
directions: Leave 1 layer of cake whole.
Cut out other layer, making rabbit ear on left side and rabbit ear from right side.
The center portion of this layer will be the bowtie.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Cook the butter and sugar together; boil 2 minutes, stirring continually.
Then add cinnamon and nuts.
Pour over the crackers that are lined in a cookie sheet (break crackers apart to fully line the cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with one 6 ounce package of chocolate chips. Cool 5 minutes, then cut into pieces and place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Cool further.

title: orange pineapple jello salad
directions: Mix water and Jell-O, stir well.
Add 7-Up and drained pineapple.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs at high speed for 3 minutes.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Blend just until combined.
Add candy.
Pour into two greased and cocoa dusted 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and completely cool.

title: crispy salmon
directions: Marinate the salmon after cutting it into strips (finger size) with lemon, salt, pepper, soy sauce and minced garlic. Add a drop of red wine, if desired. Keep in the refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup corn flakes.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add beans, chili seasoning, tomato sauce and water (depending on how thick you like it).
Cook in large pan until boiling.
Serve hot.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix all together and pour melted bark over all. Dip out on wax paper or foil.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and milk together and stir.
Then add rest of ingredients to mixture and beat well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: easy chili
directions: Spray saucepan with nonstick cooking spray. Brown ground turkey in pan. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl; add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into 3 well greased loaf pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 - 60 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups sugar, syrup and 1/4 cup water in saucepan. Boil until mixture spins a long thread.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining sugar gradually.
