Pour boiling syrup over egg whites in thin stream, beating until mixture stands in peaks. Add nuts and pour into buttered platter.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blanch the peppers and set aside. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, saute the onion in olive oil until just softened.
Add sausage and saute until browned.
Remove the skillet from the heat; add bread crumbs, cheese and egg and mix well.
Cut peppers lengthwise, then stuff with sausage mixture. Place stuffed peppers into a baking dish and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: bert's barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix vinegar, water, sugar, mustard, pepper, salt, cayenne pepper, lemon, onion and butter.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a boil. Drain to remove lemon and onions.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: zesty baked beans(microwave recipe)
directions: Total cooking time: 17 minutes.

title: quick 'n easy casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes to partially thaw.
Stir in rice, chicken or ham, soup, milk, half the cheese and onion, then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 3 servings.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in heated oven.
Place eggs, green chilies, soda, spinach (squeeze spinach dry) and flour in a blender and blend.
In separate bowl, place grated cheeses and add egg mixture; stir well. Add margarine and pour into pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Brown together onions, garlic and ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, oregano and bay leaves.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Cook noodles.
When sauce is ready, drain noodles and work in following order in oblong pan:

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch together.
Stir in rest of the ingredients and beat slightly with whisk.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Takes 35 minutes in my oven.
This pie will still be shaky, but will set up.
Do not cook over 45 minutes.

title: raisin pie(children love raisins, and they will love this pie.)
directions: Cook raisins in water for three minutes.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon; add to raisins.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add butter and lemon juice, stirring well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: no crust egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add buttermilk and milk.
Mix well, then add rest of ingredients.
This pie makes its own crust.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: cream cheese dessert(serves 10)
directions: Blend together flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix in Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Mix instant chocolate pudding with milk.
Mix until thick.
Put this on top of cheese mixture and use rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work together with hands.
Roll into medium size balls and bake 20 minutes at 400° until done.

title: carolina barbecued chicken
directions: Clean chicken and cut off wings.
Split chicken open along middle of breast bone.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Place flat, along with wings, on hot charcoal grill, turning occasionally, until done.
(You can use oven baked, broiled/browned chicken in place of grilled one, but not quite as good.)

title: easy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Top with cheese slices. Combine soup and wine. Stir well. Spoon sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cool whip-hershey pie
directions: Shave small amount off bar for top of pie.
Melt Hershey bar in double boiler.
Fold melted bar into Cool Whip.
Place in pie shell and top with shavings.
Place in refrigerator until served.

title: creamy chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chicken broth, chicken, frozen vegetables, curry and thyme.
Bring mixture to boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Whisk together milk and flour until flour is dissolved; stir into soup.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens, then simmer 2 minutes more.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Ladle into bowls and sprinkle green onion slices on top.

title: green bean stew
directions: Brown hamburger and put in bottom of pan.
Thinly slice onion on top of hamburger.
Thinly slice potatoes; add green beans, stewed tomatoes and tomato juice.
Stir together; sprinkle with a little brown sugar, salt, pepper, onion salt and garlic salt. Simmer for two hours over low heat until potatoes are done.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until light brown on top.
May be served hot or cold.

title: charcoal-grilled shrimp
directions: Combine oil, onion, wine, lemon juice, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, dill weed and salt.
Place shrimp in a plastic bag and set in a deep bowl.
Pour marinade mixture over shrimp.
Close bag. Marinate 3 to 4 hours in the refrigerator.
Drain shrimp, reserving marinade.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a rolling boil.
Drop in the cabbage leaves; blanch for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from the pot, rinse in cool water and drain.

title: chocolate layer delight
directions: Mix together the flour, butter and pecans.
Pat and spread into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: curried onions
directions: Peel onions, cook in boiling, salted water for 15 min.
In saucepan melt butter, flour, salt, curry powder and paprika. Add milk, cook and stir till thick and bubbly, stirin onions. Put in 1 quart casserole dish. Bake 350° for 35 min.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Measure cereal into large bowl.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt 5 cups marshmallows, corn syrup, butter and chocolate chips in microwave, uncovered in microwavable bowl, on High for 2 to 3 1/2
minutes, stirring after each minute until smooth when stirred.
Stir in vanilla and pour over cereal in bowl.
Mix quickly with chocolate until coated.
Stir in 1 cup marshmallows. Press mixture evenly in 13 x 9-inch pan with back of buttered spoon.
Let stand at least one hour or refrigerate if a firmer bar is desired. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: caramel brownies
directions: In a double boiler over low heat, melt 50 caramels and 1/3 cup of evaporated milk. To a German chocolate cake mix, add 3/4 cup of melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Mix well; put 1/2 of batter in a greased 9 x 13 pan and bake for 6 to 7 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and sprinkle 1 cup of chocolate chips and 1 cup of chopped nuts (optional) over the top. Pour melted caramels over that. Then distribute the remaining half of the cake mixture by spoonfuls over this. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool and cut.

title: savory salt substitute
directions: Place all the ingredients in a small electric coffee grinder, spice grinder or blender.
Grind for 10 seconds or until mixture is fine.
Insert a funnel in the top of a glass salt shaker.
Pour the mixture into it and tap the funnel lightly to fill the shaker. Cover the rest of the mixture tightly and store it in a cool, dry, dark place.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with a little onion and basil.
In shallow baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, arrange alternate layers of lasagna noodles, sauce and beef, cottage cheese, shredded cheeses and olives.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice and chili casserole
directions: Cook rice in the usual manner.
While hot, combine it with sour cream, cheese and chilies.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter and heat for about 30 minutes in a 350° oven until top is browned.
Serves 8.

title: spiced nuts
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cream of tartar and cinnamon. Place over medium heat; add boiling water.
Boil and stir until syrup spins a thread.
Remove from heat; add pecan halves and vanilla.
Stir briskly until nuts are coated.
Pour out onto waxed paper and separate with fork.
Cool and store.

title: caramel crispy squares
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with butter; set aside.
Place cereal in a large bowl; set aside.
Unwrap caramels and place them in a 1-quart glass dish.
Add marshmallows, shortening and water, stirring after each minute.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, or until shapes are melted.

title: simply wonderful, wonderfully simple
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine and stir in garlic powder.
Dip chicken into margarine and then into dry mixture to coat.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ideal salad
directions: Drain pineapple and bring pineapple juice and sugar to boil. Add 1 cup boiling water to gelatin and let cool.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Chill.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cover the carrots with water in a saucepan and cook until fork tender.
Drain well.
Add butter and brown sugar.
Cook until sugar dissolves and carrots are glazed. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: sweet sour country style ribs
directions: Cook ribs for 8
hours in a crock-pot.
Drain the juice (fat) off.
Stir the sweet and sour sauce and brown sugar together and pour over ribs.
Drain the pineapple and sprinkle it on top of ribs.
Cook 1 more hour and serve!

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Let all ingredients come to room temperature.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Beat shortening and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add extract.
Now alternately add dry ingredients and milk, ending with dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° in a tube pan 30 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool 15 minutes.
Turn out and enjoy.

title: surprise meat triangles
directions: Mix beef, cayenne and salt to taste.
Divide into 8 portions and put on a clean board.
Flatten each into a triangular shape, about 4-inches on each side.
Press cheese into center of beef. Mold and seal evenly around cheese, being very careful to cover the corners.
The edges must be well sealed or the cheese will leak out during cooking.
Beat eggs in a shallow bowl, spread out the bread crumbs on a large, flat plate.
Dip triangle into the egg, then into the bread crumbs, pressing firmly to coat evenly. Repeat a second time with each triangle.
Pour enough oil into a deep-fat fryer to come 1/2 way up the sides of the triangles. Using a slotted spoon, lower 1/2 the triangle into the hot oil and fry until browned.
Turn.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except the steak in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Cut steak in serving size pieces. Place in large roaster pan.
Pour sauce over meat.
Cover tightly and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, 1 egg and pecans.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar.
Mix until very smooth.
Pour mixture over and bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until light or medium golden.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Cut into small 1 x 1-inch to 2 x 2-inch squares and eat like crazy.

title: easy lemon fish or easy lemon chicken
directions: Melt butter with seasonings and lemon juice.
Panfry both sides until done.
This works for both fish and chicken fillets.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; cover.
Blend on high speed until ice is crushed.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry chops quickly.
Place in baking dish (single layer). Sprinkle chops with rice and in between.
Spread loose onion rings over top.
Add soup and 1 can of water.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.
Cook covered 1/2 hour more.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, honey (or syrup) and brown sugar in a bowl. Stir in milk and cereal.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Roll balls in crushed cereal.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press graham cracker crust in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat exactly 10 minutes the soft margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Spread this over crust; cut large banana lengthwise in thirds.
Lay across filling.
Drain large can of crushed pineapple and put over banana.
Spread large container Cool Whip over pineapple. Sprinkle with crushed nuts and maraschino cherry halves. Refrigerate before serving.

title: green bean lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese, egg, oregano, and green beans together; set aside. Cook noodles per instructions. In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the following until ingredients are all used: 1/3 sauce on bottom, 1/3 noodles, 1/2 green beans mixture and repeat. Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top. Pour liquid around the edges. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and buttermilk mixed with soda.
Alternate adding mashed bananas and nuts.
Spoon mixture into four 1-pound coffee cans that have been well greased and floured.
Fill each half full. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Cool before putting lids on.
May be frozen.

title: hawaiian beans and franks
directions: In large saucepan, pour 2 cans beans.
Cut franks into bite sized pieces.
Add to beans.
Add pineapple with juice.
Stir and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add milk until of desired spreading consistency.

title: split pea soup
directions: In a large pot, cover peas with water almost to top of pot. Cook on medium approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Test for softness. Peas must be soft enough to mash.
Add 1/4 cup ham base and mash. Thicken with roux.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces. Brown meat in a large soup pot in a small amount of water.
After meat has browned, fill pot halfway with warm water.
Add salt, pepper, bouillon and pot herb, then add vegetables and crushed tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for about 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with buttered roll or bread.
Add macaroni, if desired.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water and mix into mashed potatoes.
Put in a jar with a loosened screw lid and leave out on counter for 3 days.
Stir occasionally.
After 3 days, add 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup water.
Stir in and let sit for 8 hours.
Then add 1 cup flour and 1 cup water.
Stir in and let sit for 8 hours.
Now you may add 2 cups flour and 2 cups water.
Let sit for 8 hours.
From now on it may be doubled every 8 hours, but at this point there is enough starter in the jar to be used and still leave at least a half cup starter in the jar.
Store in the refrigerator and stir occasionally through the week.
Keeps indefinitely and gets better over the years.
To keep the starter going, be sure to add back to the starter equal amounts of water and flour for what was used in a recipe.
If your recipe calls for 2 cups of starter, add 1 cup water and 1 cup of flour to starter and stir in and leave out for 8 hours or overnight.
If starter is not used for over a week, stir in a teaspoon of sugar and stir well.
Store in covered crockery or glass container, not metal.

title: viva la chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove meat from bones and cut into pieces.
Cut the tortillas into 1-inch strips.
Mix the soups, salsa, onion and milk.
Place a layer of tortilla strips in casserole dish, then a layer of chicken, then soup mixture; repeat.
Top with cheese. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: apple pinwheel cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour and milk to form dough.
Roll dough out to form a rectangle.
Spread apples over dough.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Roll into jelly roll.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in butter.
Pour water and sugar over dough.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until top is brown.

title: apricot preserves turnovers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, pinch off dough and pat out in greased hand. Put 1/2 teaspoon preserves in round of dough and fold over. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best meal ever
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In an 8-inch square baking dish, layer the above ingredients in order.
Cover well with dish cover or aluminum foil; no peeking allowed during the baking.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours and serve over rice.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: out of this world dessert
directions: Mix puddings as directed on packages.
Mix the cream cheese and vanilla pudding together.
Use a 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.

title: tomato-zucchini salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, onion and cheese; toss lightly.
Cover and chill.
To serve, toss and spoon onto lettuce leaves.

title: candied yams
directions: Slice cooked peeled potatoes lengthwise in 3/4-inch slices. Arrange in single layers in baking pan.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, syrup and orange juice.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves and syrup is formed, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: homemade spaghetti
directions: Put 5 quarts water into a large pot; bring to a rolling boil. Take spaghetti and break and drop into boiling water.
Let cook for about 12 minutes or until done.
Do not overcook.
While spaghetti is cooking, take hamburger and fry.
Then drain and rinse with hot water.
Put back into skillet; add spaghetti sauce and heat.
Drain spaghetti and rinse with hot water.
Put back in kettle and pour in hamburger mixture.
Stir until mixed.

title: salad
directions: Bring to boil pineapple juice (reserved from pineapple) with enough water to make 2 cups, jello, and marshmallows. Cook until mixed well. Let cool. Add cottage cheese, cool whip, nuts, and pineapple. Chill until ready to serve.

title: bean dip
directions: Put chili beans in pot; add water.
Add minced garlic.
Add onion soup mix, chili powder and red pepper to taste.
Simmer low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Blend with sharp blade until like mashed potatoes.
Serve with chips.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs, milk
and
sugar.
Cook
rice as directed on package.
When it is done mix all ingredients together.
Put a little butter on top of rice pudding and sprinkle with nutmeg. Turn into
a
loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: jenny's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: On medium heat, saute garlic and onion in a saucepan.
Add tofu and tomatoes.
Add bay leaves, parsley and basil and heat until bubbly.

title: banquet potatoes
directions: Mix all but 1/2 stick of oleo; put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/2 stick of melted oleo. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop and mix vegetables together.
Pour Caesar salad dressing over vegetables; toss and refrigerate.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices together.
Blend all ingredients at high speed, half at a time.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix pudding with milk by directions on package until thick. Stir in half of large container of lite Cool Whip with mixer until mixed; this will be soupy.
Spread a small layer of this mixture on bottom of dish (9 x 9-inch).
Layer every other layer with graham crackers; spread pudding on crackers.
Last layer should be pudding.
Sprinkle pecans on top for icing.
Store in refrigerator.

title: busy day cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a mixer bowl, beat shortening on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add flour, sugar, milk, egg and vanilla.
Beat with a mixer until blended.
Beat 2 minutes; pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Frost as desired.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put first three ingredients in top of double boiler until melted.
Pour in mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Cream together the Ricotta cheese, cream cheese and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add the flour, alternating with the sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Shut off oven.
Open oven door and leave cake in oven for 1 hour longer.
Take out of oven; cool completely before removing from pan.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rhubarb kuchen
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, 1 stick margarine and 3 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Pat into an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Beat together 2 eggs, 1 tablespoon flour and 1 cup sugar. Pour this over the cut up rhubarb and mix.
Put into crust and bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Blend in flour and corn meal.
Add eggs, beating well. Blend in milk and flavorings. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 250° and increase temperature to 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer vegetables in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish in following order:
lettuce, celery, eggs, frozen peas (uncooked and not thawed), green pepper and onion.
Place crumbled bacon on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup. Stir and chill until thickened.
Add the remaining ingredients before gelatin sets.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.
Serves 10.

title: confederate coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add milk and unbeaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and a dash of nutmeg.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle the top with nutmeg and cinnamon mixture, nuts and sugar.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Check for doneness with a broom straw or toothpick.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes; let cool. Beat cream cheese on medium speed with mixer until light and fluffy; add 1/3 cup sugar, mixing until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over pretzel crust. Combine gelatin and boiling water in bowl, mixing until dissolved.
Add cold water and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in strawberries; pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaves and dollop with mayonnaise, if desired.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well in order given and form into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for 1 hour.
Slice and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugar; add egg yolks.
Then add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine preserves, scallion, soy sauce and ginger.
Place chicken pieces on a rack in a roasting pan and roast for 15 minutes.
Pull out pan and brush chicken with the apricot mixture.
Return to oven and continue roasting, turning and brushing chicken frequently with the apricot mixture until done, about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: devil dogs
directions: *Add 1 tablespoon of vinegar to 1 cup milk to sour.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: the marriage stew(two full servings)
directions: With the above ingredients on hand, let's get started on our happy chore of putting together a good, wholesome hearty Marriage Stew.
First, combine the 2 concerned persons with the 2 cups of love in an adequate, comfortable mixing area.
Next, blend in the understanding and patience; beat lightly with a spoon made of laughter until the mixture is smooth and fluffy.
Now, add the 2 cans of trust; pour the mixture into the casserole of life and place over very low heat to simmer.
This is also the time to add tears, dreams, touching, remembering or any other spices you feel will make your stew more exciting.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream butter with egg yolks in bowl.
Add confectioners sugar gradually, blending well.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 30 to 35 balls.
Roll in cocoa.
Store in airtight container

title: chocolate-peanut butter candy squares
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine.
Add peanut butter, confectioners sugar and graham crackers; mix well.
Press mixture into pan (at least 9 inches).
Melt third stick of margarine with chocolate chips.
Pour onto other mixture; spread evenly.
Refrigerate until hardened. Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all loaf ingredients well and top with topping.
Bake, uncovered, at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: In the top of a double boiler, melt morsels.
Add peanut butter, nuts and potatoes.
Stir.
Spoon out onto wax paper. Chill in freezer for a few minutes, or until firm.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil well.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt together and add to oil, sugar and egg mixture.
Then stir in zucchini, nuts, vanilla and raisins. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then finish cooking in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: creamy double decker fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In small microwave-safe bowl, place peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Microwave at High (100%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute, until chips are melted when stirred.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; spread evenly into prepared pan.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all together cold.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
These will keep for months.

title: yuletide salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add vinegar and sugar. Chill until syrupy.
Fold in pineapple, cheese and whipped cream. Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until thoroughly set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple salad
directions: Wash, core and cut apples into bite-sized pieces.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Add nuts and raisins and mix well.
Stir in mayonnaise thoroughly.
Chill before serving.

title: romaine salad
directions: Wash and tear romaine into pieces.
Drain olives.
Drain artichoke hearts and cut into large pieces.
Toss all ingredients together.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli as package directs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix beans together, don't drain.
In skillet, cut bacon in strips.
Start cooking, but don't brown.
Leave some grease on. Add the rest of ingredients.
Heat through; pour over beans and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes with no lid.
Yummy.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Cut 1 milk carton in half.
Cover it with 1 can of vanilla icing.
Put cookies on to make windows and a door.
Make the roof with raisins or cookies.
Use a Tootsie Roll for chimney.
Use a green lollipop for tree.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift flour, cornstarch, salt and sugar in top of double boiler; stir in 2 cups boiling water and place over other part of double boiler and boil until custard leaves the side of pan, then add egg yolks and cook 5 minutes.
Turn off heat and add vanilla and butter.
Pour in baked pie shell; cover with meringue and bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: pixie pie
directions: Blend butter, sugar, eggs, vinegar and vanilla.
Stir in coconut, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat shortening; add sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together. Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: egg 'n sausage casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter. Pour mixture into pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked brown rice
directions: Mix together, cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: extra good berry pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie crust.
Pies will be high and delicious.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: carne adobada
directions: Add salt, garlic and oregano to chili sauce.
Place strips of pork (2 x 6-inch) in the chili sauce and marinate 24 hours.
To prepare, cut into small pieces and fry in fat.
Add chili sauce to cover and cook until pork is done, approximately 1 hour at 400°.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moistened; beat vigorously 1 minute.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf, pressing gently to loosen.
Remove from pan.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Break cauliflower into sections.
Cook for 10 minutes in boiling, salted water; drain well.
Combine cauliflower with 2 tablespoons of butter, onion, cheese, sour cream and salt.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: angel delight dessert
directions: Melt chocolate morsels with sugar and salt over hot water. When melted, take from fire and add egg yolks.
Cool 5 minutes while you beat the egg whites.
Add beaten egg whites and let cool completely, then mix in Cool Whip.
Tear cake into bite size pieces; put half in pan and put about half the chocolate mixture over it.
Add rest of cake, then rest of chocolate.
Sprinkle nuts on top and store in refrigerator overnight or several hours.

title: cranberry-raspberry mold
directions: Do not drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients and put in mold or 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: thick-n-chewy cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars together.
Add eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir in oats.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and flatten on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 can tomato sauce.
Shape and put in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
For last 30 minutes, add 1 can tomato sauce, if desired.

title: crock-pot brisket
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and rub into brisket.
Put brisket into crock-pot.
(May have to cut or fold over to get it to go in, if so, be sure fat side is on top.)

title: fiesta banana cake
directions: Stir shortening just to soften; add sugar.
Then sift in 4 dry ingredients, 1/4 cup milk and bananas, mixing until well blended. Add eggs, nuts and remaining milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat until well blended again.
Pour into layer pans and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: quick salsa
directions: In food processor, finely chop all vegetables.
Place in saucepan.
Simmer until thickened.
Use on tacos, spaghetti sauce. Can be cooked in large quantity and canned in jars. Refrigerate.

title: fig bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar;
add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients
together and add alternately with evaporated milk
to sugar
mixture,
just
until mixture holds together. Divide in
6 equal
portions;
roll
one portion at a time on waxed
paper. Sprinkle
with a little flour, sugar and cinnamon;	roll
into
a circle.
Spread
fig jam on half and fold other half
over	the jam
using	wax paper.
Bake on greased sheet at
for
30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle more cinnamon and sugar on top before baking.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine sour cream, chestnuts, mayo, soup mix and onions.
Mix well.
Add spinach.
Cut small pieces, leaving just a shell.
Use to dip all fresh veggies (bite size).
Plus the pieces of torn bread.

title: carrot cake
directions: Melt butter; add Karo syrup and baking soda.
Mix well and pour it over carrot cake.
Serves 12.

title: crawfish pie filling
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and brown lightly.
Add garlic, onion, shallot bottoms, green pepper, celery and tomato sauce. Cover and fry about 1 hour.
Add 3 cups water and simmer for several hours.
Mixture should be creamy and thick when tails and fat are added.
Add tails and fat.
Cook 15 minutes, until it tails are tender.
If mixture thins, thicken by adding 2 tablespoons cornstarch, mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Add onion tops and parsley. Pour into pie shell or serve or rice.

title: cheese & wild rice
directions: Place 1 cup wild rice into 4 cups boiling water for 30 minutes. Drain. Repeat this process twice more for a total of 3 times. Add remaining ingredients to wild rice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered. Then remove cover and bake for additional 30 minutes.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut meat into serving size pieces. Pound flour, salt and pepper into meat and brown well.
Arrange in 3-quart casserole.
Place vegetables on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and add water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours. Gravy may be made from liquid before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chicken in orange juice
directions: Cut any excess fat away from chicken breasts.
Season both sides of chicken breast pieces with the salt, pepper and garlic salt.

title: pork chops with applesauce gravy
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown in a large skillet. Remove the chops and using the drippings make a thin gravy using flour and water.
Stir in applesauce.
Return chops to skillet. Scatter onion slices over and around chops.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Lightly season as desired. With mashed potatoes and a vegetable, this is a wonderful meal for a cold winter night.

title: dessert
directions: Mix milk and cherry pie filling.
Stir by hand.
Stir in cool whip.
Drain pineapple thoroughly.
Add pineapple to above items. Then add nuts if desired.
(Drink the juice.)

title: pancakes
directions: Stir all ingredients till blended. Cook on hot griddle until edges are dry. Turn and cook until golden.

title: crispy peanut brittle
directions: Cook all except soda in heavy saucepan over medium-high heat until hard crack stage (295° to 300°) or until peanuts pop open and syrup begins to brown.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir quickly and pour in hot buttered pan.
Break pieces off outer edge as candy cools.

title: garlic pork
directions: Wash cubed pork with the juice of a lime.
Place in an earthenware jar or crock.
Mix vinegar with garlic, thyme, hot pepper, salt and cloves.
Pour over pork and completely cover with liquid.
Refrigerate, covered, for 2 days.
Remove pork from marinade.
Heat oil in frying pan and fry pork until brown, about 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice flour pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat remaining ingredients. Fry in a hot, well-oiled frying pan until light golden, turning once.

title: plum breakfast cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Set aside.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, 5 tablespoons melted butter, vanilla and yeast mixture.
Pat dough into 11 x 12-inch rectangle on lightly buttered baking sheet.
Arrange plum wedges slightly overlapping to cover top of dough.
Brush plums with remaining 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cardamom.
Sprinkle evenly over top of cake.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until center tests done.
Cool to warm and serve.
Makes 16 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order in an airtight container and chill for 24 hours. Mix before serving.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Cut loaf of French bread in half, lengthwise. Mix tomato paste, Parmesan cheese, onion, olives, oregano, salt and pepper together in a large bowl. Add raw hamburger meat to mixture and spread over bread. Place on a baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Top with tomato slices and green peppers, alternating. Top vegetables with sliced cheese. Bake 5 minutes. Slice and serve warm.

title: goop
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add both eggs, cook until done; eggs will look scrambled.
Add barbecue sauce and chili beans, stir until heat completely.
Spread grated cheese on top.

title: venison chili con carne
directions: Put a couple squirrels into a cast-iron pot and cover with 1 quart of water laced with tarragon vinegar.
Simmer 2 hours.
Then dice a stalk of celery, 1 onion, a carrot and dump in.
Add generous teaspoon curry powder, bay leaf and salt.
Simmer until meat drops off bones, about 2 hours.
Fish bones out, add 2 medium diced potatoes and toss in a bunch of parsley.
If a cupful of mushrooms is handy, toss them in, make sure mushrooms are handy. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Eat hearty.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in hot oil.
Add soy sauce, salt and 1/4 c. water.
Cover and cook 45 minutes.
Add peppers and onions and cook for 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and 1 cup water.
Stir into steak mixture.
Cook until slightly thick.
Serve steak over hot cooked rice.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: rocky road frosting
directions: Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling, water.
Mix butter, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Add chocolate, stirring until blended.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Saute onion in a small amount of oil.
Add bread crumbs and crisp a little.
Combine all with salmon.
Bake in a greased casserole for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This is a dieter's delight.

title: southwestern bean soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Serve with grated cheese, chopped green onions and sour cream.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and saute onion until soft, add chicken, tomato sauce, tomatoes, salsa, garlic powder and parsley. Stir until well blended.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Place 4 corn tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour 1/3 of the chicken mixture on top.
Spread evenly.
Layer 1/3 of cheese and 1/3 of olives on top.
Repeat layers 2 more times, ending with olives on top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: prune bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir.
Add oil, eggs, buttermilk, prunes and nuts.
Stir together until mixture is smooth.
Pour into two large loaf pans (greased) or 3 small ones and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken puff casserole
directions: Butter a 9x13 casserole dish. Butter bread on both sides and place six slices in bottom of casserole dish. Combine chicken, eggs, mushrooms, olives, mayonnaise and chopped onion and place on top of bread. Cover with remaining slices of buttered bread.
Mix together soup, sour cream and sherry. Spread topping over casserole. Bake in 325 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut into small bites.
Boil macaroni separately until done.
Heat milk in large pot; do not let burn. Heat slowly.
As milk heats, add butter to melt.
Add salt and pepper.
Add chicken pieces and drained macaroni.

title: croatian cut-out cookies
directions: Mix flour and shortening. Add salt, sugar and lemon. Add eggs last. Save egg whites to brush on top of unbaked cookies.
Mix together well.
Roll out to cut into cookies.
Brush on egg whites and sugar/walnut garnish or any sprinkle of your choice to the top of the cookies. Bake in a 375° oven until light brown, 10 minutes maximum.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk, lemon juice and rind shell.
In small bowl beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing the edges carefully of the shell.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cut up any vegetables desired such as cucumbers, tomatoes, green onions, green pepper, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, in small pieces. Mix all together and let set for a day. Mix occasionally.

title: cappuccino punch
directions: In a small bowl, combine the sugar and coffee; stir in boiling water until dissolved.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Just before serving, pour coffee mixture into a 1 gallon punch bowl. Stir in milk.
Add scoops of ice cream; stir until melted.
Yield: about 1 gallon.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain.	Saute onions and mushrooms in butter in a large pan.
Add flour, salt, seasoning and pepper.
Stir well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.	Add broth.
Cook until thick.
Add cream and stir until smooth.
Add chicken and place half of spaghetti in a greased 2 qt. casserole dish.
Spoon half of chicken mixture over spaghetti.	Repeat.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven and bake for 5 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple slices
directions: Sift flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and salt together; blend with Crisco.
Add enough milk to egg yolk to make 2/3 cup liquid and add to first mixture.
Blend and refrigerate an hour or overnight. Roll 1/2 dough.
Use plenty of flour and place in a 10 x 12-inch pan.
Put corn flakes on crust.
Put the sliced apples, then 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Top with rest of dough.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, until brown.
Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice; pour on pie while hot.
Serve hot or cold.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In a boiler, bring soup to a boil.
Keep over heat and add milk, pepper and tuna.
Mix well.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour noodles in a lightly greased casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over noodles.
Top with extra cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Cut apples in medium dice pieces. Do the same with the bananas. Cut grapes in half.
Mix in a big bowl. Add 1 to 1 1/2 bowls of Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve chilled.
Great for salad or dessert.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together
in
a
bowl.
Then freeze. Set out 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas to a thin batter.	Add sugar and eggs; mix well, then
add
melted butter.
In a separate bowl, sift the salt, soda
and flour together.
Pour banana mixture into the flour bowl and mix well together.
Bake in a tin loaf at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: my mom's vanishing peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and milk until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into chocolate or graham crust.
Chill.
Delicious!

title: rio grande casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook celery and green pepper in butter until tender-crisp.
Stir in tomato paste, soup, sour cream, chiles, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Add rice.
Turn into a buttered, shallow, 2-quart casserole dish.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add vanilla.
Roll out.
Cut and bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican steak
directions: Brown steak and add to already prepared rice; simmer until done.

title: fried green apples
directions: Wash, core and quarter apples.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add apples and sugar.
Cover and cook until done (stir occasionally).

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly margarine or shortening, sugar, egg and molasses and add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Mix and roll into small balls, then roll in sugar and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: agnes' halloween treat
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, 3 eggs, vanilla and the pecans which have been chopped and floured.
Mix well. Pour into 2 loaf pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine sugar, eggs, oil, vanilla, lemon juice, salt and soda.
Add flour, apples and nuts; mix well.
Bake in preheated oven 1 hour 15 minutes.
Check after 1 hour.
Cool on rack.
Ga.
Ga.

title: steak sub
directions: Slice onion and green pepper thin.
In a large frying pan, heat oil; add onion, green pepper and sprinkle with a little oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Cut frozen steaks in thin strips.
Push onions and pepper to one side; add 1/2 of the steaks.
Cook until almost cooked.
Cut 1 slice cheese in 1/2 and lay on top of steak to melt a little.
Cut sub roll open.
Spread with mayonnaise or butter.
Put steak and cheese on, then some onion and green pepper.
Close roll and cut in 1/2.
Repeat for second roll.
Makes 4 (6-inch) subs.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix
well
the	first 4 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix
and
roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and onions.
Place in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta and cheese
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add 1 large onion, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook until onion is tender.
Meanwhile, cook seashells until done.

title: pleasant hill baked eggplant
directions: Cut top off eggplant lengthwise.
Scrape out the inside, leaving about 1/2 inch around sides and bottom of shell.
Boil eggplant meat in salted water until it is tender.
Drain completely and chop.
Saute chopped onion in butter and add chopped parsley.
Mix with eggplant and mushroom soup; add seasonings.
Mix with enough crumbled crackers to make a good stuffing consistency.
Pile filling back into eggplant shell. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Heat the blueberries and sugar until sugar melts.
Place blueberry mixture into a greased 9 x 13 glass pyrex.
Cover this with the pineapple.
Sprinkle the cake mix over this mixture. Drizzle the melted margarine over the cake mix and top with the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook rice in boiling water until partly done.
Mix all ingredients, except cabbage.
Separate cabbage leaves; wash and parboil in salty water until slightly tender.
Cool cabbage leaves.
Take big spoonful of meat mixture and put in center of cabbage leaf and roll up.
Place in baking dish that tomato soup or sauerkraut has been adding.
Bake in 325° oven until meat is done, about 1 hour.
Cover when placing in oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 4 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling, salted water.
(Add 1 tablespoon cooking oil to noodles to keep them from sticking together.)
Drain noodles when tender. Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Layer half of noodles, Ricotta filling, half of cheese and half of meat sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo in double boiler over hot water. Remove from stove; stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Turn out onto a sheet of buttered foil that is lined with coconut.
Roll into a roll.
Or, line a loaf pan with buttered wax paper and coconut. Pack candy into pan; let cool.
Cut into slices.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over bread and let stand until bread is soft.
Add eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, raisins and vanilla.
Mix. Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a moderately slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until lightly browned and a silver knife, when inserted, comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: In shallow dish, place flour.
In large, shallow baking pan, place margarine and insert in heated oven until melted.
Dip chicken, one piece at a time, in flour, turning to coat, then place, skin side down, in margarine in baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: ever-lovin cake
directions: Mix by hand the first 6 ingredients (including pineapple juice).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
While cake is cooking, mix remaining four ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil and pour over cake as soon as it comes out of the oven.
Serve warm.

title: graham cracker salad
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter; press down in baking dish.
Save some crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Bake just a little and let cool.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water; cool to lukewarm.
Beat cream cheese and whipping cream until very stiff; add sugar, pineapple, vanilla and fruit cocktail.

title: confetti-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.	Drain.	Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in casserole dish and top with French fried onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered until last 10 minutes of baking.

title: tart barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in a saucepan over low heat and cook until butter melts, stirring constantly.
Keep warm in a double boiler until ready to use on barbecued meats or as a sauce for barbecue sandwiches.
Makes 1-3/4 c. sauce.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and meat in a little hot fat.
Add drained beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, bay leaf, dash of paprika and dash of cayenne.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, adding reserved bean liquid or water, if needed.
Makes 6 servings.
Serves 6 to 8.
Cooking time is 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna twist salad
directions: Prepare rotini as directed on package; drain.
Add tuna, peas, celery, radishes, onion, pimento and dressing.
Cover and chill. Before serving, toss gently.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in food processor until they resemble dirt. Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together until smooth.
Layer in plastic or glass flower pot (9 x 13-inch pan if you do not have a new unused flower pot).
Start layers with crushed Oreos, then cream cheese mixture, then chocolate pudding ending with enough Oreos to cover the entire top.
Chill and serve with a spade or spoon.
If you serve this in a flower pot, stick plastic or silk flowers in the top of it.
It's a great conversation piece.

title: easy refrigerator vinaigrette slaw
directions: Chop all finely; put in large bowl with lid and pour dressing ingredients one at a time over top without mixing.

title: home-style meat loaf
directions: Combine all four ingredients and press into casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: raisin pie
directions: Add water to raisins and simmer until about 1/4 cup liquid remains.
Add vinegar and butter; cool.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; stir into raisins.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar, and mustard in a bowl.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1 cup sauce mixture in a bowl.
Mix well.
Place in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour remaining sauce evenly over loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in salted boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrot. Fold in squash and onion.
Combine stuffing and butter.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Spread remainder of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
This is a great dish for a crowd.

title: chunky cheese spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in skillet until no longer pink.
Remove chicken from pan; drain all but 1 tablespoon oil.
Add zucchini, peppers, mushrooms, onion and garlic to skillet.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until crisp-tender.
Add chicken and spaghetti sauce.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Add the cheese.
Cook and stir just until cheese melts.
Pour sauce over cooked spaghetti. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: dill pickles
directions: Let set 90 days.
Heat lids.
Open and wash through 2 or 3 waters.
Slice round and cover with 2 cups sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Let set overnight.
Put in jars.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Add bananas and nuts.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 375°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put margarine in pan and add berries.
Mix together for batter the remaining ingredients well and pour on top of hot berries and butter.
Bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Scrub squash.
Cut off ends.
Do not peel.
Slice to make 6 cups.
Cook, covered, in small pan of boiling salted water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Sprinkle with salt. Reserve a few slices of squash for garnish.

title: carrot and broccoli stir-fry
directions: In large wok or skillet, heat oil.
Add garlic and ginger. Stir-fry 15 seconds.
Add broccoli and carrots, tossing to mix well.
Add broth and cover pan.
Cook for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Remove cover; turn heat to high and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
When veggies are cooked, stir in soy sauce. Remove from heat and sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: salsa
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Drain some of juice off.
Mix and simmer 40 minutes.

title: chicken squares
directions: Add beaten eggs and onion soup mix to chicken broth.
Combine with other ingredients.
Pour into a greased oblong pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Fruit: blueberries, banana slices, Mandarin orange sections, seedless grapes, strawberry halves, kiwi or any fruit you want,

title: cheese and chili dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remainder of ingredients.
Chill.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: autumn vegetable saute
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic. Cook and stir on medium heat until onion is tender.
Add zucchini and mushrooms.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, salt, oregano and pepper.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese just before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven browned potatoes
directions: Parboil the potatoes, keeping them whole throughout the recipe.
Remove from pan and deep-fry in grease.
Roll potatoes in equal parts oregano and Parmesan cheese mixture.
Salt and pepper them to taste.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: dan quayle's potato soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan and cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Do not drain.
Chop until medium fine. Add milk.
Season to taste.
Serve hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine the bananas and sugar. Mix in egg and oil. Add dry ingredients. Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Roll in crumbs and refrigerate eight hours.
Re-roll in crumbs and fry in 1/4 inch of oil until brown.

title: italian chicken
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, line chicken, making several slits across chicken with sharp knife.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. Take chicken out of pan.
Pour out broth.
Return chicken to pan. Making sure the slits in chicken are open, pour 8 ounces of salad dressing over chicken.
Cover with foil, return to oven 20 minutes.

title: whipped topping
directions: In a small pan, sprinkle gelatin over water; heat slowly, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Pour into a small mixing bowl; add sweetener and vanilla and cool.
Add chilled milk; beat at high speed until very thick.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Refrigerate several hours for best flavor.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into greased deep pie dish.
Drain peaches, saving juice.
Place peaches over mixture in dish.
Mix cream cheese with sugar and juice.
Spoon over peaches leaving 1/4 inch rim around edges. Sprinkle cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes, cool 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: kacie's homemade pepperoni rolls
directions: On a lightly flowered surface (which has been sprayed with PAM) roll out dough.
In a medium bowl mix cream cheese and parmesan cheese.
Add pepperoni, onion, and garlic powder.
Mix well and spread evenly over dough.
Roll up dough tightly (like jelly roll). Cut into slices and place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: meat-cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain well.
Add tomatoes and chilies.
Simmer uncovered for 45 minutes.
Add cheese in chunks and heat until all cheese is melted.
Serve hot with favorite chips or raw vegetables.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch or Bundt pan (greased and floured) for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage and onions until pork is brown.
Drain and return to skillet.
Add soup and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes. Spoon into greased casserole.

title: water chestnut rumaki
directions: Wrap chestnuts in bacon and secure with toothpick.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 300° for one hour.
Drain fat.
Combine catsup, sugar and soy sauce.
Pour over chestnuts.
Sauce need not completely cover.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Try to keep toothpick clean for people to serve themselves.

title: cream cheese delights
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Refrigerate 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Press pie crust into mini muffin pan and bake until slightly brown; let cool.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour cookie sheets.
In small bowl, beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form. Beating at high speeds, sprinkle in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla (whites should stand in stiff, glossy peaks).
With rubber spatula, fold in coconut and flour.
Drop by tablespoons about 1 inch apart onto cookie sheets.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove with metal spatula.

title: almond puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture.
Mix with fork.
Round into ball; divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into a strip 12 x 13-inches.
Strips should be about 3 inches apart.
In medium saucepan, heat 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water to rolling boil.
Remove from heat; quickly stir in almond extract and 1 cup flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat.
Beat in eggs all at one time, until smooth.
Divide in half; spread each half evenly over strips, covering completely.
Bake about 60 minutes or until topping is crisp and brown.
Cool.
Frost with glaze and sprinkle generously with chopped almonds.

title: weight watchers snickers dessert
directions: Soften ice cream and Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients and mix with mixer.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put in freezer for at least 2 hours.
Cut in squares.

title: caramel roll topping
directions: Place 1/2 of dough in small pieces in a greased pan.
Combine ingredients for caramel sauce.
Melt and pour 1/2 over the bread. Spread with nuts.
Add the rest of dough in pieces.
Cover with the remaining caramel sauce.
Let raise until double.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn upside down and cool.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil your sweets
until done, drain and peel.
In a greased casserole add brown sugar (pack down on bottom), place the sliced sweets on top of the brown sugar.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of sweets again if you wish.
Dot with butter.
Add water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 or more.

title: lemon crisp cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter baking sheets.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add lemon, flour and oats.
Mix until oats are well blended.
Place dough formed into balls onto baking sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until light brown. Yields 38 (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Mix flour and cornstarch together.
Flour chicken and set aside.
Mix egg and milk.
Soak chicken in mixture 10 minutes.
Re-dip into flour and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Mix bouillon cubes, 1 cup water, sugar, soy sauce and cornstarch until dissolved.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Cook rice according to directions.
Place chicken and rice on plate.
Cover with sauce, cashews and onions.
Use more soy sauce if desired.

title: party dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight. Serve with nachos or Fritos Scoops.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip, lime juice and food coloring.
Pour into pie crust and chill for about 4 hours.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cover bottom of skillet with oil.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until onions are transparent.
Add oregano, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and 2 cans of water per can of paste and sauce (6 cans).
Add pepperoni and mushrooms.
Simmer for 1 hour or more.
Makes enough sauce for 3 pizzas.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Form in shape of choice. Drain off all grease but a small amount.
Pour tomato soup and diced tomatoes over meat loaf and place in oven and bake until soup is boiling.
Or add 2 cans Franco-American mushroom gravy mix and place in oven until gravy is boiling.
Bake 1 to 2 hours. Check the center for doneness.

title: diet fruit salad
directions: Take fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges. Drain and save juice.
When drained, add orange juice.
Then add sliced bananas.
Mix all drained
juices together and add slowly to the fruit along with 1 large box sugar-free vanilla pudding to desired thickness. Chill (will not need all the juice).

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first five ingredients very well.
Put half cornmeal mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer ground beef, cheese, pepper and onion.
Pour rest of mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Beat tomatoes in blender for a few minutes.
Season with the following spices to taste:
salt, pepper, parsley, fresh basil (chopped) and oregano.
In a heavy pot, brown garlic in oil; remove.
Add tomatoes, sauce and spices.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Skim oil from top of sauce.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Season meat with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Chop up onions and peppers.
Add to meat.
Roll meat into quarter-sized balls.
Roll in flour.
Shake excess flour.
Add enough grease to a pan to cover meatballs.
Let meatballs brown.
Drain them on paper towel.
Cook egg noodles.
Drain.

title: toast baskets
directions: Cut crust off bread slices.
Generously spread butter on one side of each slice of bread.
Press buttered sides down into large muffin pan cups.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until toasted.
Fill with fresh fruit or jam.

title: meat-stuffed peppers
directions: Remove top and seeds from green peppers; parboil 5 minutes; drain.
Halve peppers.
Brown onion and meat; add tomatoes, corn and seasonings.
Heat through.
Place peppers in 9 x 13-inch pan and stuff and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cool rise rolls
directions: Combine dry yeast, water and 2 tsp. sugar and set aside. Combine oil, sugar, water and salt.
Add the yeast mixture. Gradually add flour until a soft dough.
Let rise until double; punch down and let rise again.
Punch down and put into pans or make into balls about the size of golf balls.
Let rise overnight in a cool place.
Bake at 400 for 10 - 12 minutes for rolls.

title: raspberries and cream
directions: Cut oleo into flour and sugar until crumbly.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: kosher pickles
directions: Boil first three ingredients.
Pack jars with next four ingredients.
Pour boiling mixture into jars up to 1/4 inch from top of jar.
Put small amount of alum into each jar.
Be sure to wipe off top of jars after pouring in vinegar mixture.
Seal immediately.
Set hot jars into water bath until hot through and through.
Do not allow hot jars to touch or set on cool surface.

title: beans and pasta
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Mix well, cook 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break up cake in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Mix all other ingredients except glaze and strawberries.
Cut strawberries up in glaze.
Spread over top of cake mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat butter in oven at 350° in small oblong casserole.
Pour in sliced peaches.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk and pour over peaches.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown.
Cool and eat.

title: quick meat loaf for 2
directions: Combine milk, egg and stuffing crumbs in bowl.
Let stand 2 minutes. Add onion and beef.
Mix well.
Place in shallow baking dish and shape into 2 small loaves. Top with barbecue sauce. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
For 4 to 6 servings, double all ingredients but use 1 egg.

title: easy cheese cake pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, or until outer edges of pie begin to crack a little.
Center will set upon standing.
Refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours or overnight before serving.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Add water to make one cup. Combine beet juice, sugar, vinegar and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil. Pour hot liquid over beets.
Cover and let stand several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Crust:
Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until foamy.
Add sugar (2 tablespoons at a time), beating well after each addition.
Then continue beating
to very stiff peaks.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan to form nest-like shell; build up sides to 1/2-inch above edge of pan.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 50 to 55 minutes.
Turn off oven and let cool overnight.

title: chicken on rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup with milk; reserve 1/2 cup.
Mix remaining soup mixture with rice, mushrooms (including liquid) and half of onion soup mix.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour reserved mushroom soup on top; sprinkle with remaining onion soup.
Cover and bake 1 hour; uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: dip
directions: Melt butter and add all the other ingredients. Heat and put in chafing dish with candle under to keep hot. Serve with fresh peeled apples.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Measure liquid; add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add Jell-O to mix.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into flat pan or Corning Ware dish.
Cover; put in refrigerator until firm. Combine cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla; spread over congealed salad.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: cheese ring
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients together and shape into a ring. Refrigerate until chilled, after covering with seal wrap.
When ready to serve, fill center of ring with strawberry preserves. Serve with Triscuits or crackers of your choice.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Mix well the sugar, oil and eggs, then add other ingredients. Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee tins.
Fill each can 1/2 full and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Let cool before removing from can.

title: nut roll
directions: Place yeast in small bowl.
Add sugar and lukewarm cream.
Let stand while mixing butter into flour.
Blend butter as for pastry until consistency of coarse cornmeal.
Make a well in center of mixture and drop in unbeaten egg yolks.
Add yeast mixture at same time and mix dough thoroughly until dough leaves sides of bowl. Mix for about 5 minutes.
Place dough on lightly floured board and cut into 4 pieces.
Let rest while making filling.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed, using low-fat milk (2% or less). Mix in sour cream and whipped topping.
Can layer with bananas and cookies or just mix all together.
This makes a very large dessert.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake until well mixed.
Set aside.

title: kraut salad
directions: Toss ingredients together.
Cover and chill 4 to 12 hours. Toss again before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix together apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix together flour and butter.
Flatten in plate.
Add apple mixture.
Cook 5 minutes at 4°.

title: chicken with fideo
directions: Combine 1/2 cup water, 1/2 slice onion and chicken breasts in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Water in pan should be absorbed.
Add Fideo and simmer until the Fideo turns lightly brown.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups water, adding your spices and your 8 ounce tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Removing the cover, simmer 10 to 15 minutes until water is absorbed.

title: whiskey cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs; blend.
Add flour and soda.
Add dates, walnuts, raisins and whiskey.
Batter is very stiff.

title: shrimp dip(serve with chips)
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: beef or pork barbecue
directions: Simmer all together for 1/2 hour.
Serve on hamburg buns.

title: cheesy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
I use my hands, clean of course! Leave in container and refrigerate until chilled.
When cold, shape into a ball (or divide into smaller balls) and roll in ground pecans.
Nuts can be chopped any way you want them.
I divide the mixture into 4 balls sometimes!

title: bill blass' meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix meat and set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add celery and onions; cook until soft, about 10 minutes.
Add celery and onion and all other ingredients to meat mixture, except chili sauce.
Combine well and form into a loaf.
Place meat loaf into baking dish and top with chili sauce. Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with all other ingredients.
May add pecans, if desired.
Chill and serve.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Defrost ground meat.
Mix all ingredients together in large pot, except water.
Add 1/2 to 1 ketchup bottle of water to mixture to get desired consistency.
Cover and cook for 2 hours over low-medium heat.

title: stove top tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse.
Mix
remaining
ingredients in a separate pan and heat slowly
until cheese melts.
Mix with noodles and serve. Most children love this dish.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes (do not overbake; cookies will be soft.)
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla and baking soda; stir real good and pour onto the popped corn.
Put in roaster; bake for 1 hour plus in a 200° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.
(When pouring syrup onto corn, mix real good to coat.)
Continue stirring occasionally after removing from oven so it will not be in one large chunk. Let cool completely before storing.
The corn is very crunchy.

title: ham & cheese mash potatoes
directions: In a small bowl, mix potatoes and garlic salt, then spread it in a 1 1/2 qt. greased baking pan.
Sprinkle ham over potatoes.

title: vegetable garden dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with raw vegetable dippers.
Store dip, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: lemon pineapple pie
directions: Make one pie shell.
Let cool.
Cook lemon pudding according to box directions and cool slightly.
Cut cream cheese into small pieces and mix with slightly warm lemon pudding.
Add crushed drained pineapple.
Put into pie shell and refrigerate.
When pie is cool and set, you can add whipped cream over the top, if you wish.

title: oatmeal cinnamon drops
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs, molasses and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon and soda; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins, nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown or 12 minutes.

title: ice cicles
directions: Fill ice cube tray with water or anything you would like.
Put a popsicle stick into each cube, laying the stick to the outside of the tray.
Freeze, then wait, then have fun.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, butter, vanilla and sugar.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: crab dip(great with crackers.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight. Serve over crackers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In casserole dish, combine soup, milk and pepper.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 can of onions.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine all vegetables in large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain vegetables thoroughly.
Press out liquid.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pack hot relish into pint jars.
Seal with lids. Process 10 minutes in boiling water.
Yield: about 4 pints.

title: old fashioned shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together twice.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add egg to milk and add all at once to dry mixture.
Mix until dough leaves sides of bowl.

title: justin wilson's corn bread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix corn bread and toast in large bowl. Pour in stock.
Set aside.
Over medium heat in skillet, heat the oil and saute the parsley, celery, onions and green onions until the onions are clear, then pour into the bowl with the bread.
Add the mint, salt and pepper and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased casserole dish or stuff a hen or turkey and bake 60 minutes or until bird is done.

title: self frosting oatmeal cookie
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Use waxed paper to roll dough into 2 to 3-inch diameter rolls (usually 8 to 10-inches long).
Chill.
You may freeze dough for later use.
Slice into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Dip each slice into a small bowl of confectioners sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: bundt breakfast cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream with vinegar, vegetable oil, hot water, instant pudding and flavoring together for 2 minutes. Grease Bundt pan.
Make mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour batter into Bundt pan alternately with cinnamon mixture, making layers.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork; add beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Add sugar, shortening and milk.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture.
Fold in nut meats.
Bake in well-greased bread tin in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes; cool.
For easier cutting, this bread is better made the day before it is to be used.
Good sliced thin and spread with cream cheese.

title: corn stuffing
directions: Mix the corns, egg, bread crumbs, pimiento, salt and pepper. Fill roast 1 hour before done.
Place remaining stuffing in casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake alongside crown roast at 325°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in pan on stove and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute, take off heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on foil or wax paper and cookies will harden as they dry.
(If too thin, add more oatmeal.)

title: shrimp thermidor(en casserole or crepes)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare rice.
Keep warm.
In medium skillet over medium-high heat, cook shrimp and celery in butter. Stir constantly.
Remove 6 shrimp for garnish.
Reduce heat.
Stir in flour.
Mix until well blended.
Gradually stir in half and half, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened and shrimp are tender.
Put rice in casserole.
Top with mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and garnish with shrimp.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts and is hot.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 2 small loaves or 1 big loaf.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box.
Mix cottage cheese and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour in Jell-O mold and freeze.
Use directly from refrigerator.

title: queen of pies
directions: Stir together sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Blend egg yolks and water; gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in butter, lemon rind and juice.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Cut and core apples- Cut into quarters. LOOK FOR SEEDS AND STEMS!! Put all into a pan over Medium heat, covered. Simmering for 15 minutes. Let apples cool, then mash.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; place in greased casserole.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese over this, then cover with the bread crumbs that have been tossed in melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: crab (or shrimp) bisque
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and boil gently 5 minutes.
Add cream soups and crab or shrimp. Simmer 5 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in evaporated milk. Reheat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.

title: orange pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt, orange rind, lemon juice and orange juice.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add slowly, beaten egg yolks and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
