Cover with meringue from the 3 egg whites and brown in oven.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place the chicken in bottom of casserole dish. Pour the vegetables over chicken. Mix well the soup, chicken broth and bouillon cube and bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables. Pour crust over top of this and bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and cut lettuce and onions into small pieces.
Fry bacon in skillet.
Remove bacon and crumble into tiny chunks.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste and sugar on top of lettuce.
Add vinegar to lettuce.
Make sure that the bacon grease is still very warm, then pour over lettuce.
Mix well.
Serve with brown beans and cornbread.

title: macaroni-cheese in new casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute green pepper lightly in butter.
Add flour, stir well and add milk.
Continue stirring until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Add salt, pepper, 2 cups Cheddar cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Continue to cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Combine with macaroni in 2 quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar and 2 tablespoons Parmesan. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Chill potatoes.
Add celery, 3 tablespoons vinegar and salt; toss lightly.
Place sour cream in small mixing bowl.
Add coddled eggs, remaining vinegar, pepper, mustard, garlic and onion; mix well.
Pour dressing over potato salad; mix well. Chill for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: jean nickel's baked beans
directions: Bake, uncovered, in a slow oven for 2 or 3 hours.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, shortening and egg until smooth.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Add to sugar mixture; stir in hot water and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 40 to 45 minutes.
If using self-rising flour, omit soda and salt.

title: bubble solution
directions: Stir lightly.
Leave sit overnight.
Make loops of stiff wire. Let kids have fun, even grown up kids.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and take all meat from bones.
Dot bottom of baking dish with butter.
Spread chicken in dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup with flour and 2 cups chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Slice boiled eggs over top.
Roll biscuit dough out very thin (1/4 inch thick) and cut biscuits out and lay on top of chicken. Bake at 375° until dough is brown.

title: shrimp boil
directions: Bring water
to boil in large pot.
Add seafood seasoning
and a	little	salt.
Put sausage in first.
Ten minutes later,
add potatoes.
Ten
minutes
later,
add corn on cob. Continue to boil about 10 minutes, then take everything out of pot
and
put
in the shrimp.
Allow them to simmer only a few minutes until they turn pink.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put rice in large baking pan or roaster that has been well-greased.
Mix soups and milk and pour over rice.
Mix all of this well.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of rice and soup mixture. Sprinkle with onion soup.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight or same number of hours.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, covered.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix and put in two round greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Spoon strawberries in between layers and on top.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Good.
Good.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and onion.
Place potatoes in well greased casserole dish with lots of butter.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in half of margarine.
Add milk, soup, sour cream, seasonings, potatoes and 2/3 of cheese.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with remaining cheese on top.
Sprinkle on corn flake crumbs.
Drizzle remaining melted margarine on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Good warmed over but you can halve the recipe.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add cake mix and flour.
Knead; let rise until double.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with butter, cinnamon, nuts and sugar.
Roll and cut into 3 dozen rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add marjoram, salt and paprika.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Add meat and brown.
Pour in wine; cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add water sparingly while cooking.
Serve with noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Beat and set aside.
Mix condensed milk with Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures.
Alternate layers of pudding and bananas and vanilla wafers.
Crumble wafers on top.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Beat first four ingredients until smooth.
Pour into oblong baking pan or 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, ginger and baking powder.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix molasses and buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll out on lightly floured surface; cut 1/4-inch thick (1/2-inch for softer cookie).
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In large bowl, stir in flour, soda and salt; mix.
Add other ingredients, except candy; mix well.
Chill dough for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into small balls.
Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake until light brown.
Remove and place kiss into the center of the cookie. Cool, then remove from cookie sheet.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, then let cool.
When it begins to thicken, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan and let set.
Slice into squares and serve.

title: friend recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients with a generous helping of God's love and you are sure to make a new friend.

title: beef tartare(hamburger mixture)
directions: In large bowl, using 2 forks, toss all ingredients.

title: butterbarn rolls
directions: Scald milk and remove from heat.
Add shortening to milk. Combine yeast and sugar in bowl.
Add yeast mixture to lukewarm milk mixture.
Add salt and slightly beaten eggs to mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Let rise until double in size, about 2 to 3 hours.
Place half of dough on floured board; roll into circle 1/2-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut into 16 pie shaped wedges.
Roll each wedge beginning at round edge and place on greased pan with pointed end underneath.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake about 15 minutes in 400° oven.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: dolly beck's russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Work in the flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set but not brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool; roll in sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream together oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Turn into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
No frosting needed, but can frost or serve with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate-peanut butter chip pie
directions: Prepare peanut butter chip crust.
Measure peanut butter chips into mixing bowl.
Blend melted butter, 1/4 cup sugar and cocoa until smooth in second bowl.
Set aside.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar in medium saucepan; add milk.
Beat egg yolks slightly; add to gelatin.
Cook and stir over medium heat until gelatin is dissolved and mixture lightly coats a spoon.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Immediately pour 1 cup hot mixture into peanut butter chips.
Stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Add remaining hot mixture to cocoa mixture.
Stir until smooth with wire whisk.
Chill both mixtures until partially set. Pour chocolate into pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Fold into peanut butter mixture.
Pour onto chocolate layer.
Chill completely.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: green tomato ketchup
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions and cabbage when ground into a bag and squeeze out juice
or
drain
overnight.
Let vinegar, sugar and other seasonings
heat,
then
add other ingredients and cook 30 minutes.
Stir,
fill
jars and seal.
Makes about ten pints. This is an old recipe and very good.

title: hot chili
directions: Cook ground turkey in 2 or 3 cups water, stir while cooking. Season with salt and pepper.
Drain, leaving 1/2 cup of water in turkey.

title: berry krunch
directions: Mix all ingredients except berries and ice cream.
Put half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread evenly.
Press in slightly softened strawberry ice cream. Top with remainder of dry mixture. Store in freezer until ready to serve. Add thawed berries to top. Serves 15.

title: best cheese cake
directions: Combine eggs, cheese, sugar, salt and extract; beat until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and put into Graham-Nut crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and chill 4 to 5 hours.
Serves 10.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; stir well.
Pour into pastry shell; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes, or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Good, good!

title: sourdough corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Scald milk; pour over corn meal and cool to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan. Bake in a 425° oven for 40 minutes.

title: mexican cabbagelos alamas, new mexico
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add other ingredients and soy sauce to taste.
Cook on low until cabbage and squash are cooked, approximately 20 minutes.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 1 cup juice.
Combine pineapple, remaining fruit and pecans in large bowl.
Toss gently.
Combine pudding and the reserved pineapple juice in mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit and pecans and mix gently.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Pour the hot dressing over the vegetables, cover tightly and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving. Makes about 15 servings.

title: potato kugal
directions: Dice bacon and onion; brown in butter in skillet. Grate potatoes.
Put in eggs, milk and salt; stir well.
Put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve with sour cream.

title: sausage and hash browns pie(makes one 10-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine potatoes, margarine and bouillon.
Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch pie plate; press on bottom and up side rim to form crust.
Bake 25 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In large skillet, cook sausage and onion; pour off fat.
Stir in eggs, cottage cheese and cheese food pieces.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, oleo and peanut butter together.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Stir gently.
Pour powdered sugar in brown bag. Pour in Chex Mix and shake well.
Put in bowl and serve.

title: hidden valley hot potato salad
directions: While still warm, cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Gently toss together all ingredients except chives, saving them for garnish. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: pesto
directions: Place all ingredients in processor and blend until smooth. Serve over your favorite pasta.
Cover Pesto mixture with 1/4-inch layer of olive oil and freeze or refrigerate up to 6 months.

title: salmon loaf or patties
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving liquid.
Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients. Spoon into oiled pan.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.
Unmold and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Shape in ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans and chill.
Serve with crackers.
For variety, you may roll cheese ball in chopped almonds or finely chopped parsley.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, salt and spices and beat well.
Blend in pumpkin and salt.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: champagne cake
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, make Jiffy cake as directed on box.
Mix together cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread mixture on cooled cake and refrigerate.
Drain can of pineapple and spread on cake. Spread Cool Whip on top of everything.
Can be made the day before.

title: luncheon meat pinwheels
directions: Spread all slices of the meat with either of the cream cheeses.
Roll first slice, then join meat edges to begin second slice.
Roll all in groups of two until all meat is rolled to make a log.
Wrap with waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and serve on rye bread (cocktail style) or on crackers.
To add variety, place sweet pickles or your choice of olives in the center of each roll before rolling up.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the boiling water and oatmeal and cool. Cream the brown sugar and butter or oleo. Add the eggs and oatmeal mixture together.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add sifted ingredients.
Place batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover batter with the chocolate chips, chopped nuts and coconut. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine cake mix, water, eggs, butter, brown sugar and nuts in bowl.
Mix well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Spread in 2 greased and floured wax paper-lined pizza pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.
Cool.
Spread with whipped topping. Arrange any fruits over topping.
Heat apricot preserves and water.
Pour over pizza.
Chill until serving time.
(A real hit.)

title: pork adobo
directions: Place the pork in a saucepan.
Add vinegar, garlic, pepper, soy sauce and water.
Cover the saucepan and cook slowly until meat is tender and most of the broth has evaporated (about 1/4 cup remains).
Serve hot over steamed rice.

title: bell pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions together.
Pour boiling water over enough to cover and let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil all together 5 minutes.
Put into pint jars and seal.
Can be frozen also.
Makes about 8 pints.
Very good.

title: italian sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Carefully remove mushroom stems; set stems aside.
Spray a 13x9x2 inch baking dish lightly with non stick vegetable spray.
Place mushroom caps in dish open side up. Set aside.
Combine sausage and garlic in a heavy skillet.
Brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain any excess fat.

title: l. h. inn salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
(Make it 24 hours ahead.)

title: mamie's cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese; stir in vanilla and sugar. Beat until creamy. Add milk to make frosting of spreading consistency. Serve small slices. Very, very rich!

title: microwave even easier candies
directions: In 2-cup glass measure, melt chocolate on High until shiny; stir until smooth.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken in salted boiling water.
Cool.
Cut up in bite-sized pieces.
Steam broccoli.
Spray Pam on casserole dish. Spread out cooked broccoli pieces; salt and pepper.
Pour on melted butter; squeeze lemon over broccoli.
Add 1/2 grated cheese.
Put chicken pieces on cheese and broccoli.
Mix milk and soup together and pour over casserole.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Remove when cheese is starting to brown.

title: salsa for little latin meat balls
directions: Heat all ingredients in 1-quart saucepan, stirring occasionally, until hot.
This dish may be made in advance and kept warm in the chafing dish or a crock-pot.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar. Add Cool Whip; stir until smooth. More juice may be added to thin a little. Serve with fresh fruit, such as strawberries, grapes, pineapple, bananas, peaches, apples, etc.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground meat and mix other ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Better if served the next day.

title: icebox sandwiches
directions: Put eggs, sugar, juice and salt in saucepan.
Boil 3 or 4 minutes or until thickened.
Mix in package of Jell-O.
Stir and mix well.
Whip canned milk, using lemon juice if necessary.
Pour in Jell-O mixture; stir good.

title: stuffed cabbages
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage and cover for 1/2 hour.
Cut around cabbage heart and pull off leaves.
Brown ground beef. Cook and drain rice.
Add to hamburger.
Add egg, onion and seasonings.
Place hamburger mixture in cabbage leaves and roll up separately.
Secure leaves with toothpicks.
Place rolls in casserole dish and pour tomato sauce over all.
Cook slowly on top of stove for 2 hours.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in small amount of margarine.
Brown onion in 1/2 stick margarine.
Combine all in casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Change casserole by adding pork chops.
Brown pork chops lightly and place on top of rice before baking.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Beat in oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add carrots.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour in 3 greased cake pans.
Add flour.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Let come to a boil and cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and let cool.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in a 5-quart pot.
Add soups and milk and heat on medium.
Do not boil.
Add broccoli and continue cooking on medium about 10 minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese and heat until melted. Season to taste.
Stir often to avoid bottom from scorching. Makes 6 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and brown sugar.

Blend into cream mixture the flour and salt, then mix in chocolate chips and nuts. Press into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until light brown; cut while warm. Cool before removing from pan.

title: quick chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion, chopped garlic, salt and pepper and drain.
Add beef to a big pot.
Add pinto beans.
Add tomato soup.
Add crushed stewed tomatoes and chili powder. Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put all ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil.
Cook about 8 minutes and into casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.

title: millionaire salad
directions: 1. Mix together well and pour into dishes.
2. Freezes well. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine zucchini, oil and beaten egg; mix in flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cocoa. Add the vanilla and chocolate chips. Mix well. Spread batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef, adding salt, chili powder, pepper and beef bouillon cubes.
Drain fat, add all beans, tomatoes and sugar; cook 20 minutes.
Mix flour and water until smooth.
Add to chili and cook on medium heat for 10 more minutes.

title: cabernet pot roast
directions: Dredge meat in flour and salt.
Brown meat on all sides in oil.
Pour in tomato sauce, water and wine.
Add herbs.
Cover and simmer gently for 3 hours in a 325° to 350° oven.
Remove meat; thicken sauce for gravy.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Slice pickles into long quarters or use dill slices.
Replace them into original jar.
Add other ingredients and cover.
Let stand room temperature for 24 hours.
Shake often to dissolve sugar.
Refrigerate.
Pickles will be crisp and almost like bread and butter pickles.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cooked squash and cream of chicken soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add crumbled cornbread.
Add seasoning. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar; blend well.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While cake is still hot, pour hot topping over cake in pan and let cool.

title: filbert loaf
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Make a well.
Slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar, honey and nuts.
Put in well and work.
Form sausage like rolls.
(Don't make rolls too high.
If they are slightly flat, they will cook better inside.) Place 2 rolls in each pan.
Beat one egg and brush the logs.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or longer.
(Logs may be browned and look done before time, but do not take out of oven.
They will not be cooked inside.)
Cool and then slice.
Makes 8 logs.

title: rich lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press into bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Line with wax paper, grease wax paper.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in prepared pan; set aside.
Combine cake mix and next 3 ingredients in large bowl according to directions on box.
Spoon batter over coconut and pecans.
Combine cream cheese and margarine in saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring often until margarine melts and mixture is smooth.
Stir in powdered sugar until smooth.
Spoon mixture over batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Invert cake on serving platter and remove wax paper.

title: berry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large container and chill in refrigerator.
Just before serving, pour into punch bowl.
Float orange and lime slices on top.
Makes 22 (6 ounce) servings.

title: baked cheddar cheese olives
directions: In a small bowl,
work together cheese with oleo.
Add flour and cayenne.
Work the mixture until well blended.
Wrap mixture around large olives (stuffed ones).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fisherman's macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni shells in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
Drain salmon liquid into 1-pint cup.
Add enough milk to make 2 cups.
Flake salmon.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour, seasoned salt, instant onion, black pepper and dry mustard.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add 1 cup of the cheese.
Stir until melted and blended.
Fold in macaroni, salmon, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, sour cream, peas and minced parsley.
Turn into a greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Place in well-greased Bundt pan.
Combine oleo, cinnamon and brown sugar; heat on stove until well mixed.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy apple raisin cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in a mixing bowl and let stand 10 minutes.
Blend oil, vanilla and egg with the apples, then combine the dry ingredients.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and bake 40 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 20 minutes or until brown.
This dish may be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix together sugar, beaten eggs and melted margarine. Add flour, pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool, cut and take out of pan (greased 9 x 13-inch pan).

title: velvet chicken
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with dried beef.
Wrap a piece of bacon around each piece of chicken and secure with toothpick. Lay chicken on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour on top of chicken.
Bake uncovered at 250° for 4 hours or at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vinaigrette(potato salad with beets)
directions: Dice the potatoes, beet and carrot.
Slice the cucumber and chop the pickled cabbage.
Add chopped onion.
Make a dressing with the rest of the ingredients and pour over the salad.
Mix well. Garnish with slices of hard-boiled eggs or diced, cooked ham to make a complete one-dish meal.

title: stuffed pizza(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 450°. Brown meat.
Drain and set aside.
Mix baking mix and water until dough forms.
Divide dough into 2 parts, one slightly larger.
On a surface dusted with baking mix, roll larger ball of dough into a 16 x 14-inch rectangle.
Place in dish.
Pres into bottom and sides of pan.
Sprinkle dough with 1 cup of cheese.
Cover with 3/4 cup of sauce.
Add meats and other toppings.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Roll remaining dough into a 9 x 13-inch rectangle.
Put over cheese, pressing edges together to seal.
Make small slits in crust.
Spread with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake for 22 to 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Start layering with first tomatoes, macaroni, then cheese, ending on top with cheese.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Pour milk into 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole until about 3/4 full.
Cook between 350° and 375° until done, about 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: diane's stuffed cabbage
directions: Peel cabbage leaf by leaf trying not to break leaf.
Place in boiling salted water and cook until tender, drain.
Mix ground meat with rice, egg, salt, pepper and garlic salt or powder.
In center of cooked cabbage leaf place a small handful of meat mixture in center of leaf.
Roll cabbage, tucking in sides and fasten with toothpicks.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan, pour tomato sauce on top of cabbages.
Sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese. Cook in 350° oven, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix altogether in bowl.
Spread in well-greased pan and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cut in about 30 minutes and remove from pan.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding, then add the rest.
Let sit in the fridge 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: cherry jubilee sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve over ice cream.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: cube steak and gravy
directions: Brown cube steaks in skillet.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in whatever you want the soup to be in last (3-quart pot).
Saute onion in butter (medium heat).
Blend in flour (lower the heat; this will make a rather thick paste).
Add the milk (it has to get hot to thicken, but not boiling).
Choice: You can chop the broccoli by hand and add to the pot along with the chicken broth or I use my blender to really mush it up good with the chicken broth and then add it to the pot.

title: sweet and sour barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add all other ingredients and simmer until thickens. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: aunt yvonne's fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Add sliced bananas, peeled and chopped apples, cut grapes and cut up peaches.
Then add drained mandarin oranges, miniature marshmallows and pecans.
Mix in 1/2 pint sour cream.
Add coconut, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: nana's  b'nana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 25-30 minutes at 350 F. I like to substitute 1 c applesauce for the shortening.
It works well baked in a bundt pan well greased and sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar.

title: sam and logan's big chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in chips and nuts. Press into pan (either use 2 regular pizza pans or one 9 x 13-inch baking pan that have been sprayed with Pam).
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: whistling bagpipes
directions: Melt together chips and peanut butter.
Add marshmallows and noodles.
Drop onto wax paper in tablespoon size.
Chill.
Makes about 35 pieces.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Mix as many kinds of fruit as desired.
Add dry vanilla pudding and mix well.

title: batter for chicken or fish
directions: Egg, flour, make, cocoa, chocolate, suar.
Ster it up foar 4 hours.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: In a medium bowl combine all ingredients except ham.
Spoon mixture evenly over each ham slice.
Roll up over filling.
Secure each roll-up with a toothpick.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Arrange vegetables in layers:
rice, corn, peas, beef and so on.
Cover dish and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 20 minutes longer.
Four to six strips of fried, crumbled bacon may be added to top of casserole when you take it from the oven.

title: self frosting brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare mix according to package directions.
Spread evenly in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Spread marshmallows over brownie dough.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over marshmallows, then sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.
Cool before cutting.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all ingredients together and stir.
Put lid on casserole and put in oven. Cook at 350° to 370° until done.

title: lo-cal honey mustard chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing 1 hour; broil.
Serve with steamed broccoli with 2 teaspoons lemon juice.

title: snow-capped broccoli spears
directions: Cook broccoli spears according to package directions; drain well.
Arrange broccoli with stem ends toward the center on an ovenproof platter or in a 9-inch pie plate.
Brush broccoli with the melted butter or margarine.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites and salt with rotary beater until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Gently fold in mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Spoon mixture in center of broccoli; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir in creamed mixture.
Stir well.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: seven day sweet pickles
directions: Day one:
Wash cucumbers and cover with boiling water.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13 pan.
Do not grease pan.
Top with a cream cheese frosting. (Pecans can be used in place of walnuts.)

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 1
1/2 hours or until done.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine, oil, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased (Pam) cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in large soup pot and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over artichoke shells or steamed brown rice.

title: apple mallow yam bake
directions: Toss apples and nuts with combined brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate layers of apple mixture and yams in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with margarine. Cover. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Top with marshmallows. Broil until lightly brown. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Mix flour and 1 cup sugar in separate bowl (mix thoroughly).
Add 1 cup water to sugar/flour (start stirring and don't stop).
Add mixture to boiling water (keep stirring). Cook until thick (keep stirring).
Remove from heat.
Add Pet milk (rinse each can with a small amount of water and continue to stir).
Add 2 cups sugar (keep stirring).
Add beaten eggs (keep stirring).
Add vanilla (keep stirring).
Follow the directions on your freezer for freezing.

title: microwave baked maple bananas
directions: In medium size microproof baking dish, cook butter on High for 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in maple syrup.
Place bananas in dish; coat well with butter mixture using spoon.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Turn bananas.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Sprinkle with lemon juice and serve warm.

title: oreo bread pudding
directions: Mix bread cubes and broken cookies in large bowl.
Set aside.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and chocolate. Add sugar, cream, corn syrup and vanilla. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat. Serve warm or cold over ice cream or pound cake. Refrigerate leftover. Yields 3 1/3 cups.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni 6 to 8 minutes or tender; drain well.
Add undrained tomatoes, mushrooms, oregano and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until macaroni is tender and moist of liquid is absorbed.
Pour into a serving bowl and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marjorie wright's hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: frozen strawberry dessert(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into a large mixing bowl and beat on high for 15 minutes. Watch carefully (may overflow). Lower speed. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: lemon apricot cake
directions: Mix.
Bake in tube pan at 350° about 1 hour.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in saucepan.
Add water and boil for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Cool completely.
Add oranges (drained) and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: dracula's blood(drink for halloween)
directions: Mix fruit punch and apple juice.
Add 7-Up right before serving.

title: challah bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 3 cups flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat 2 cups water, sugar, butter and salt just until warm (115° to 120°) and butter is almost melted.
Stir constantly.
Add flour mixture; add 3 eggs.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can; mix in with a spoon.

title: john's cake
directions: Cream all ingredients together until a creamy consistency, then add eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate fillers
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar and salt.
Blend in flour and oats until particles are fine.
Press about 2/3 of mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat condensed milk in saucepan.
Stir in chips.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough on pizza pan, sprayed with Pam.
Mix cream cheese, sugar
and vanilla together and spread on cookie dough. Beginning
with
outside
make
a complete circle with slices
of each
type
of
fruit until you reach center.
Mix marmalade
and orange juice and brush on top of fruit.
Chill in refrigerator a short while, then slice like a pizza.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add onions and rice.
Saute until brown.
Add worcestershire.
Stir in chopped mushrooms and liquid.
Stir until boiling.
Pour into a baking dish and bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Stir everything together.
Spoon into a small ovenproof dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.
Serve with corn chips, toasted pita, bagel triangles.

title: pie shells
directions: Blend flour, shortening and salt.
Add egg, water and vinegar. Mix well and add to flour mixture.
Divide in thirds.
Roll on floured board or pastry sheet.
Makes 3 shells or 1 shell and 1 two-crust pie.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes at 400° or until golden brown. Makes about 12 muffins.

title: strawberry meringue pie
directions: Sprinkle 2 tablespoons cracker crumbs on bottom of well-greased 9-inch pie plate (reserve rest).
Beat egg whites until foamy; add tartar and salt.
Beat until stiff peaks form. Gradually beat in granulated sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until very stiff.
Beat in vanilla until blended.
Fold in pecans and cracker crumbs.
Spread over bottom and sides of pie plate.

title: rich chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crushed cornflakes on top and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ambrosia bread
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until lemony.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add last four ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased loaf pans, small or large.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine first 7 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth. Mixture will be very thick.
Cover and cool.
Fold in sour cream. Pour into pie shell; chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: onion-tomato soup
directions: Peel and slice onion thinly.
Saute in butter in large saucepan.
Add tomatoes, broth and spices.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Serve with French bread.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seeds.
Place cut side down in a baking dish in 1/2 inch of water.
Bake at 400° until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of sugar, flour and nutmeg and sprinkle over apples.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: apple-butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
In large mixing bowl, mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, butter, apple butter and milk until blended.
Add nuts and raisins. Combine all ingredients until moistened.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Freezes well.

title: south america polloal cazador
directions: Mix 1 hour before serving.
Mix salt, pepper and flour together and coat chicken.
Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Now stir in ingredients.
Simmer lightly 40 minutes until almost done.
Stir in drained chickpeas.
Cook until peas are heated well and chicken is tender.
Makes about 5 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add soup, water and rice.
Stir well.
Add broccoli and cheese to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey breast and mushroom casserole
directions: Butter bread and break into bite size pieces.
Use half to line bottom of greased, 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine and add vegetables and mayonnaise.
Spread soup over top and mix eggs into mixture.
Top with remaining bread and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In baking dish, layer cooked and boned chicken, sour cream and soup.
Prepare Stove Top dressing as directed on package. Put over soup.
Bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: fruit fluff pie
directions: Beat together condensed milk and lemon juice.
Blend this mixture into thawed Cool Whip.
Fold drained fruit into this mixture.
Pour into pie crusts and chill until ready to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar; bring to boil.
Add jello right from box.
Mix well.
Set aside to cool to room temperature.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Fold in whipped topping.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve over lettuce leaves.

title: nut and poppy seed rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water with sugar.
Let stand while you mix margarine and flour as for pie crust.
Make a well, then add egg yolks, salt and yeast mixture.
Mix until smooth and dough leaves the sides of the bowl.
Cut into 4 pieces and roll out as thin as possible.
Spread filling and roll.
Place on greased pans.
Let raise for 1 hour, then brush with egg whites.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
When baked, cover rolls with dampened cloth for 10 minutes.

title: creamy orange dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat until smooth.
Serve with strawberries and angel food cubes.

title: cream pecans
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream in pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugars are dissolved.
Cook until medium soft ball forms when tried in water.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until a light sugar coating begins to form on nuts.
Turn out on wax paper.
Separate nuts by hand as you put on the wax paper.
Let cool.

title: fantastic broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add soup, cheese and broccoli.
Cook together and serve warm.

title: tropical garden punch
directions: Freeze all but the soda and lime. Add soda and fresh lime slices just before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour three bread pans.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry dessert salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add frozen raspberries and stir until thawed.
Stir in pineapple and banana.
Pour half into 8-inch square pan and refrigerate 30 minutes; spread sour cream over gelatin, then pour remaining Jell-O over the sour cream.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook, clean and devein shrimp.
Cook celery, pepper, onion and garlic in shortening until tender.
Add all other ingredients except shrimp and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot over hot cooked rice.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: she crab soup
directions: Place eggs in a 2-quart saucepan and cover with water. Bring water to a boil. Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove eggs from hot water and cool. Press the yolks of hard-boiled eggs through a sieve and set aside. In a large pot, melt the butter over medium-low heat. Add the green onions and celery; cook, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are soft, about 4 minutes. Add the flour and cook and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in the stock, milk and cream. Bring to a simmer. Add cooked egg yolks, crabmeat, sherry, salt and pepper and heat through. Ladle into bowls and garnish each serving with a pinch of paprika and a lemon slice.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
In a mixer, combine the butter and shortening and beat on low speed until well mixed.
Add the sugar gradually and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in the eggs, milk, orange juice and vanilla.
Add the flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and fifteen minutes.

title: herring dip
directions: Drain herring, cut into small pieces.
DO NOT use onions from jar.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Serve on crackers or cocktail rye.

title: italian sausage and mushroom strata(brunch entree)
directions: Butter a 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish. In a large skillet, heat sausage, onion, mushrooms and scallions for about 20 minutes or until sausage is cooked through and vegetables are tender. Drain off fat. Arrange half of the bread cubes in the prepared baking dish. Spread half of the sausage-vegetable mixture over the bread cubes. Sprinkle half of the Cheddar cheese and half of the Parmesan cheese over the top. Repeat layers.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: Brown gizzards and livers in oil until done.
Add onion, green onions, garlic, salt, parsley, celery and bell peppers.
Stir-fry for about 2 minutes on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Do not overcook.
Vegetables should be a little crispy; drain if necessary.
Add red pepper.
Pour this mixture into a large bowl. Add cooked rice; mix well.
This will taste better the next day.

title: good soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine potatoes, water, salt and margarine.
When it starts to boil, stir in dry soup.
Simmer over low heat approximately 20 minutes.
Can add tomatoes.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake until done.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Line bottom of pie shell with Swiss cheese.
Top with broccoli.
Beat together and pour over broccoli: eggs, half and half, flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle pie with shredded cheese. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fish sauce piquant
directions: Add the garlic, bay leaves, Worcestershire, peppers, salt and cloves to the water in a 6 to 8-quart saucepan; bring to a boil and lower heat to simmer.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a large bowl, sift together all ingredients. Add sour cream, egg and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Add apples and mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes. While pie is in the oven, prepare the topping.

title: mushroom-broccoli casserole
directions: In saucepan, bring broth and broccoli to boil.
Reduce heat; cover, simmer 5 minutes and set aside.
Cook mushrooms and onions in margarine.
Blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until thickened.
Cook and stir two more minutes.
Add broccoli and broth, corn and pimento.
Heat 3 to 4 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Place drained yams in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Place rest of ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Pour mixture over yams and bake 15 more minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Over low heat simmer raisins, dates, dried fruits, cherries, hot water and cherry juice.
Beat eggs, add Crisco, sugar, molasses, dry ingredients and then add the fruit and water ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, soup, cheese, eggs and crackers.
Dot on top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and food coloring.
Set aside. Whip cream in a separate bowl.
Add to cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and blend by hand.
Pour mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish or in individual muffin tins lined.
Freeze. Great!

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add the egg and beat.
Add the molasses and mix.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Using a mixer add the dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls (inch in diameter), placing on cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass bottom that has been dipped in extra sugar.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool; store in airtight container.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and dry pudding.
Blend in pecans and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
(It keeps well.)

title: potato skillet dinner
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Salt and slice potatoes.
Dice onion in a large skillet.
Drain red beans and mushrooms; add to potatoes.
Add drained hamburger to mixture.
Mix all of these ingredients.
Pour mushroom soup over mixture.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are cooked.
Stir mixture as needed while cooking.

title: confetti spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, cook onion and garlic in butter and oil until light.
Add salt, pepper and basil. Add vegetables.
Cover and reduce heat to medium-low.
Let cook until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat. Stir in soy sauce. Add cooked spaghetti. Add cheese slowly and toss well or cheese will clump.

title: corn casserole
directions: Do not drain anything!
Mix together and cook for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir twice.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in covered casserole dish. Bake for 2 hours. Add carrots and potatoes. Bake for additional hour. Serve from pot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Place spinach, soup mix, onion and water chestnuts in food processor bowl fitted with metal blade, cover.
Process until spinach is finely chopped.
Remove mixture from food processor and place in a medium bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise and sour cream.
Cover and chill overnight.
To serve, cut off top of bread.
Remove bite size pieces of bread from inside of loaf, leaving about a 1/2-inch shell.
Tear top into bite size pieces.
Fill bread shell with spinach mixture.
Place on a round serving plate and surround with bite size bread pieces for dipping.

title: spiced coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients except coffee in saucepan; heat to boiling.
Strain mixture; pour liquid over coffee in heatproof container and stir until coffee is dissolved.
If desired, serve with twist of lemon peel or a cinnamon stick.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Blend cake mix (dry), peanut butter and brown sugar in large mixer bowl on low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup of the crumb mixture.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Husk corn.
With sharp knife split corn kernels cutting lengthwise of corn kernels.
Then, with back of knife, scrape out kernels until you have 2 cups corn pulp. Combine with salt (or unseasoned salt), cream and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.
Serve hot with butter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: snicker bar pie
directions: Cream butter; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in Snicker bars.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: bob's shish-ka-bob
directions: Mix salad dressing according to directions on package.
After washing and draining meat, place in flat casserole dish.
Pour dressing over meat; place in refrigerator for at least 6 hours. The longer it marinates, the more tender the meat.
Place meat and vegetables on shish-ka-bob stick and grill about 12 minutes per stick, turning a 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.

title: pronto spanish rice and beef
directions: Brown onion, pepper and beef in frypan. Drain fat. Add water, tomatoes and seasonings. Bring to a boil and boil about 2 minutes. Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle casserole with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Yields 6 servings.

title: episcopal punch
directions: Mix, drink and be merry and have a designated driver.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Cut apples into thin slices.
Place in baking dish or a deep pie plate.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar, salt and cinnamon. Pour water over filling and dot with butter.
Roll pastry to 1/8 inch thickness and place over apples.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 50 minutes, until apples are tender.

title: walnut vegetable medley
directions: Cut beans into 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Pare and slice carrots. Cook vegetables separately in salted water just until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.

title: zucchini and pasta soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Saute onion.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer until pasta is done.
Serves 4.

title: cole slaw(the kind that lasts for weeks!)
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper, onion and carrot all together (food processor does great!).
Put salt over mixture and let stand 30 minutes.
Squeeze out all juices.
Pour boiling vinegar and sugar over mixture.
Refrigerate.
Lasts for weeks.

title: greek tacos
directions: Mix together well all the ingredients and stuff pita bread. Enjoy!!

title: crock cheese
directions: Mix together and form a ball; keep in small crock jar.

title: rouladen
directions: Trim away fat and bones from steak.
Cut into sections approximately 3 x 5-inch.
Salt.
Place bacon on meat.
Add onion and, if desired, a strip of dill pickle.
Roll and fasten with toothpick or tie with string.
Roll in flour.
Brown in oil in large roasting pan on all sides.
Add water to 2 to 3-inches. Simmer on burner or place in 325° oven for 2 hours or until done.

title: caramel ice cream
directions: In heavy skillet, brown 2 cups sugar, stirring constantly until caramelized, being careful not to scorch it.
Immediately combine eggs, remaining sugar, flour and milk in a large saucepan. Smooth out any lumps and bring to a boil.
Carefully add caramelized sugar and stir constantly until mixture is melted. Remove from the heat; add vanilla.
Pour into the cylinder of an ice cream freezer; add enough whipping cream to fill cylinder 3/4 full. Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Yields about 1 gallon.

title: sticky buns
directions: Let bread dough set out for 45 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Combine vanilla pudding, butter, brown sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and milk to make syrup.
Cut bread dough into 15 pieces each loaf.
Place syrup on the bottom of pan to cover, then nuts and raisins.
Place other 15 pieces of dough down; add more syrup, nuts and raisins.
Place other 15 pieces of dough on top; add more syrup, nuts and raisins.
Put dishcloth over pan; let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes for a metal pan and 30 minutes for a glass pan.

title: peach or apricot butter
directions: Drain fruit and remove pits; puree fruits using blender or food strainer.
Pour into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on high 8 to 10 hours.
Remove cover during last half of cooking.
Stir occasionally.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: lasagna
directions: In large skillet, cook onion and pepper, then add hamburger meat and mushrooms until done.
Drain drippings and add oregano, basil, soup and water (simmer 15 minutes).
Cook noodles until tender and layer pan with noodles, sauce and cheese until all gone.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat waldorf salad
directions: Toss ingredients and serve.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Crush ice in a towel with hammer or rolling pin.
Place lemonade concentrate, strawberries and crushed ice in blender. Process on low speed until ice begins to blend into mixture Increase speed to high and process until smooth.
Makes 3 cups; 73 calories per 1 cup serving, 0 grams fat, 0 mg. cholesterol.
One cup equals 1 serving of fruit.

title: no-egg wonder cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until almost smooth.
Pour into 2 greased and floured or greased and wax paper lined 9-inch round or square pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream, or it may be iced.

title: ham and cheese puffs
directions: Put water and butter in saucepan and bring to boil.
When butter has melted, add flour and salt all at one time.
Reduce heat to low and stir with wooden spoon for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring vigorously after each addition.
Divide mixture in half. Stir ham into half of mixture and cheese in the other.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Beat eggs and salt with evaporated milk; add skim milk and Sugar Twin.
Cook on top of double boiler until mixture is thick. Add vanilla; mix well and remove from heat.
Toss sliced bananas with lemon juice and arrange on bottom of chilled graham cracker crust.
Pour pudding over bananas and chill until firm.
Top each serving with a dab of whipped topping if desired.

title: mixed veg-all salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add 1 large heaping tablespoonful of Miracle Whip and 1/2 teaspoon of mustard.
Mix well.
Let set for awhile.
Chill and serve.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: *With the Ro-Tel tomatoes alone, this dish will be relatively mild; add jalapeno peppers to taste.

title: boursin
directions: Process garlic and butter for 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: mandarin orange peaches
directions: Drain peaches and mandarins in separate bowls; reserve syrups. Process mandarins in a blender until smooth.
Combine mandarin syrup, brown sugar, cornstarch, marmalade and salt, in a saucepan.
Gradually heat, adding reserved peach syrup and pureed mandarins.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add peaches; simmer 5 minutes, gently turning peaches several times, add the liqueur.
Serve as a dessert or side dish for pork.
Serve warm or chilled.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marzetti
directions: Place cooked spaghetti in large greased casserole.
In separate pan, brown beef; drain fat, and add onion, salt, pepper and soups.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cheese and mix to melt.
Mix this mixture with spaghetti.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, then add corn oil, sugar and zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick 'n easy chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Lightly sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt, pepper, paprika and garlic salt.
Brown in melted oleo.
Add cream of chicken soup, water (blended together) and 1 teaspoon parsley flakes.
Also add a dash more of garlic salt. Cook covered until chicken is tender.
The soup makes a delicious gravy of its own and this is very good served with herbed rice. This can be prepared the night before and cooked, then heated slowly when ready to serve.
Great for working women.

title: potato soup
directions: In saucepan, cook potatoes and onions until tender, leaving enough water to cover potatoes.
Add cream, celery soup, butter and mushrooms.
Cook on low heat 20 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: winter sauerkraut salad
directions: Build this salad however it suits your taste.
Be careful not to use too much dressing.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine cake mix, gelatin, oil, nectar and egg yolks; beat until light.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 325° oven for one hour.

title: rio vista balls
directions: Cut a 1/2 to 1-inch thick slice from top of cheese.
Using a spoon, scoop out cheese, leaving a firm shell.
Spread cheese very fine and measure.
Should yield 1 quart.
Combine cheese with sour cream, wine and grated onion.
Beat until fluffy and well blended. Stir in green pepper, pimiento and seasoned salt.
Pile lightly back into the cheese shell.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda twice.
Place in small bowl.
Beat sugar and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add butter and mix into egg mixture thoroughly.
Add sour cream, water and vanilla and beat.
Add flour mixture and cocoa; beat slowly.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in chocolate chips and pour into buttered Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sift powdered sugar on top.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in apples.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco corn-rice salad
directions: Combine salsa, vinegar, pineapple juice and chili powder in bowl, then mix with rice and let cool.
Add pineapple, corn, olives, tomatoes, pepper and onion and toss well.
Line a shallow serving bowl with salad greens.
Toss salad into bowls and serve with tortilla chips.

title: cool whip vanilla ice cream
directions: Blend sugar and sweetened condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip; stir.
Add the milk and vanilla.
Put in electric ice cream freezer.
Add a layer of ice and a layer of salt until freezer is full.
Add more ice and salt as it melts.
Freezer is done when it stops.
(Blended strawberries, peaches or bananas may be added if you prefer a different flavor.)

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Place cream cheese, cottage cheese and mayonnaise in mixer bowl and beat on high until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and beat until combined. Chill and serve with crackers or bread.

title: granny pew's brown rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, saute chopped onion in margarine.
Add rice, beef broth and consomme. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until liquid is absorbed (approximately 20 to 25 minutes). Serves 4.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Crush wafers until crumbs.
Add nuts.
Divide in half.
Cream butter, egg and powdered sugar together.
Fold the pineapple into whipped cream.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix melted butter and graham cracker crumbs together.
Pat on bottom of a spring-form pan.
Mix softened cream cheese, heavy cream and sugar.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time! Add cornstarch and vanilla.
After mixing, pour on top of crumb crust in spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Shut off oven and leave cheesecake in for an additional hour.
After cooling, top with cherries and refrigerate before serving.

title: diann's vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix together.
Pour into casserole dish. Melt 1 stick margarine; add 1 pack Ritz crackers (crushed).
Mix together.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: auntie lisa's pizza dough
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Add oil, 3/4 teaspoon salt and flour; mix.
Add flour as needed.
Dough must be soft, not sticky.
Knead.
Put in lubricated bowl; lubricate surface of dough.
Cover; let sit for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Great with all kinds of fresh fruit, especially strawberries.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir in molasses.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir after each addition.
Stir in oatmeal.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper to cool.
If mixture becomes too thick, add a little milk and stir well.

title: applesauce cake(sugar free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix boiling water, baking soda and add vinegar into unsweetened applesauce.
Add to first eight ingredients and mix well.
Bake approximately 25 minute.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
While hot, add cubed Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Crush crackers and pour on top of broccoli and cheese mixture.
Pur melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.
Use a 7 x 11-inch glass dish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: butter brickle bars
directions: Mix
softened
butter, one egg and cake mix; stir until crumbly.
Press
in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Mix the rest of ingredients and pour on top of bottom layer.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, cocoa, cream and vanilla.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and oats.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: nutty spinach casserole
directions: Place spinach in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole. Cover.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes or until spinach is heated through, stirring twice during cooking.
Drain well.
Stir in soup until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 12 minutes or until set in center, rotating dish twice during cooking.
Serves 6.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine brown sugar, mustard and vinegar; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add 1/2 of sugar mixture; mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Pour other 1/2 of sugar mixture over ham loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy baked ratatouille
directions: Lightly grease a shallow 1 1/2-quart ovenproof dish with 1 teaspoon oil.
Cover bottom with half the onions and garlic.
Set aside.
Slice off ends of eggplants and cut in half lengthwise. Place each half on a cutting board, skin side up.
Slice each half lengthwise into thirds, leaving slices attached at stem ends. Spread sliced section apart to make a fan.
Insert a tomato slice between each section of eggplant fans.
Layer fans in dish along with remaining tomato, onion, garlic, mushrooms, basil, rosemary, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Press down to pack.
Drizzle with remaining oil.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until eggplant is tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: meat and tater pie
directions: Mix ground round and onion soup.
Mix until well mixed.
Add pepper, allspice and milk.
Spread evenly into pie shell.
Top with thawed hash brown potatoes.
Spread over meat mixture.
Top with second pie shell.
Seal and flute.
Cut small slits (4 to 5) in top crust.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 325° or until meat mixture is completely done and crust is a golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: tonnerelli
directions: Saute ham and mushrooms in butter until browned.
Cook noodles as per package directions; drain.
Cook peas; drain. Put all hot ingredients in large mixing bowl, sprinkle with cheese and toss well.
Serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with margarine.
Add sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla, milk, salt, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: soyameat vegetable loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly in a large bowl.
Pour into a loaf pan or shallow casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until firm and lightly brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple macaroon
directions: Fill 9-inch pie pan with apples. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, flour and margarine until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: spanish scramble
directions: Scramble veggies in margarine until soft.
Mix egg with skim milk.
Scramble in egg and serve with salsa.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed. Mix well with butter. Spread 3/4 mixture in a greased Pyrex casserole dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top (can use chicken breast).
Add drained mushrooms.

Mix together remaining vegetables, lemon juice, salt, sour cream, cream of chicken soup and 1/2 of chicken stock. Spoon over chicken and sprinkle remaining dressing mix on top. Pour remaining chicken stock over top. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: coke roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place roast in bean pot (or covered roasting pan); cover with Coke and soup.
Bake, covered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until internal temperature reaches 170°.

title: winter potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook, unpeeled, in boiling salted water about 30 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and peel.
Slice warm potatoes about 1/4-inch thick into a large bowl.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix together and roll the size of a walnut.

title: betty smith's brownies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In heavy saucepan, combine butter, shortening, cocoa and coffee.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar; add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well, using wooden spoon or high speed electric mixer.
Pour into well buttered 11 x 17 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Pour frosting over brownies as soon as they come out of oven.
Cool; cut into 48 bars.
Enjoy!

title: southwestern dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together reserving some tomatoes, olives, and green onions for garnish.
Bake in serving dish.
Bake 20 minutes until bubbly in 350° oven.
Top with garnish and serve with chips.

title: roasted tomato salsa
directions: Heat a large cast-iron skillet over medium heat. Add whole tomatoes, jalapenos and garlic. Cook 15 minutes or until tomatoes are blackened, turning frequently.	Remove from pan; cool slightly.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Semi-freeze for ease in slicing.
Slice with the grain into 1/8-inch strips.
Marinate overnight in glass dish, thoroughly covering the meat with sauce made from other ingredients.
Lay strips of marinated meat in single layer on oven racks.
Placing a cookie sheet underneath will catch drippings. With oven door opened a crack, roast at lowest possible temperature (125° to 140°) for 8 to 12 hours.
Taste occasionally until desired chewiness is attained.
Keep in covered jar.
Yields 1/2 pound of jerky.

title: cranberry-cheese pie
directions: Put milk, lemon juice, vanilla and cheese in the blender container; blend until mixture is smooth.
Set aside a few whole cranberries from sauce.
Fold remaining sauce into cheese mixture. Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with the reserved cranberries.

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Combine and cook 7 minutes after it comes to a rolling boil. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: three layer cookie
directions: Grease and flour three 8 x 11-inch pans.
Mix eggs and melt butter.
Mix flour, sugar and extract together with electric mixer until smooth.
Divide batter into 3 bowls (equal amounts). Add red food coloring to one, green to the other.
Place batter in each pan and bake for 15 minutes (or until done) in 375° oven. Cool.
Spread strawberry jelly between layers.
Melt chocolate and spread on top and sides.
Refrigerate until hard, then cut into squares.

title: chicken chili
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces. Cook chicken, onion, green pepper and garlic in oil in a large saucepan until chicken loses pink color. Add remaining ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and top with grated cheese and sour cream. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: uncooked play dough
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add water slowly to make a pliable mixture.
Add oil to prevent hardening.
You can add a few drops of food coloring to the water for color before adding it to the flour and salt.
Mix it all up.
A good way to mix: Sit down on the kitchen floor with a big bowl with your preschooler and start to pour it together!
Store in plastic container or plastic bag that seals well.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush 2 rows of cookies.
Mix with ice cream and Cool Whip. Pour into crusts.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: crispy chicken bake
directions: Melt margarine and shake in desired amounts of salt, pepper and paprika.
Prepare chicken pieces.
Dip chicken pieces in margarine and roll in the mixed potato chips and corn flakes. Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle any remaining crushed chips and flakes on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender, with a sheet of aluminum foil placed lightly over the chicken.
When chicken is tender, remove foil and bake until brown.

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine beef with beans and heat on low 5-10 minutes.
Heat cheese soup. Layer chips, beef and bean mixture, cheese sauce, lettuce, tomato, green onions, and sour cream for individual servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together. Beat well.
Pour into greased mold.
Bake 1 hour in covered roaster (set in pan of hot water).

title: harvest cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in bowl; stir often.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes in tube pan or 2 (4 x 8-inch) bread pans.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Sprinkle chicken with Lawry's salt and pepper; brown in oil in large frying pan or electric frypan.
Remove from pan.
Chop onion; brown in butter in same pan.
Add mushrooms.
Add a dash more Lawry's, pepper and garlic powder.
Remove from pan.
Melt bouillon in hot water in another pan.
Add tomato paste, thyme, parsley and wine; mix well.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Put chicken back in pan; pour sauce over.
Cover; cook at low temperature for 45 minutes (220° on electric frypan).
Serve over plain white rice.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Add all of the ingredients to 2 sticks of melted margarine and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Mix well and shape into small eggs.
Melt 12 ounces of chocolate chips and 1/3 stick of paraffin over double boiler.
Dip eggs into chocolate coating.
Place dipped eggs on buttered cookie sheets and place in refrigerator for a few minutes to harden.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Crumble sausage and cook until browned.
Drain fat.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheese (optional:
add either onions, green pepper or mushrooms).
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper. Pour over other ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If optional ingredients are added, additional baking time is required.

title: summer coolness
directions: Cream the flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Gently mix in crabmeat.
Split English muffins and spread halves with mixture. Cut each half into quarters.
Freeze for at least 1/2 hour.
Broil until they are bubbly and golden brown.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/2 cup of sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, topping mix and cold milk.
Spread the crumb mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2 dish; add half of the cream cheese mix.
Spread on pie filling; add remaining cream cheese.
Top with crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serves 12.

title: pork chops piquant
directions: Heat butter in frying pan.
Season chops with salt, garlic powder and cumin.
Brown chops.
Add green onions and saute.
Add green chili salsa.
Cover pan and simmer 1 hour or until tender. Stir in yogurt.
Taste and adjust seasonings if necessary.
Makes 2 servings.

title: koulourakia(greek butter cookies)
directions: These cookies are great with coffee!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt
butter
in
skillet
and cook onion until tender. Stir in
flour,
then pour in broth.
(Stir until thick.) Pour in chicken
and
vegetables
and heat until bubbly.
Put into dish and
top with biscuits.
(These can be homemade or canned biscuits.) Bake at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: quick chinese casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onions and put in casserole dish.
Layer peas, sprouts and mushroom soup.
Put noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fudge crackle cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger simmer
directions: Brown hamburger patties.
Drain fat.
In a separate saucepan, boil 2 cups of water with salt.
Stir in rice; bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to a simmer; cover rice for 20 minutes.
Pour mushroom soup over hamburger patties with 1 can of water.
Simmer until rice is done.
Serve with or over rice.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Combine candy, nuts and coconut.
Add 1/2 of the flour mixture.
Cream margarine until light.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each one.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour mixture.
Add candy mixture and mix well. Bake in large tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: touchdown cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream first 6 ingredients until fluffy. Sift dry ingredients together.
Gradually stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped peanut butter cups.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from sheets and cool on wire racks.
Yields approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread and crumble; set to 1 side.

title: coconut cake
directions: In sheet cake pan, bake cake.
When cool, use fork to stick holes in cake and pour condensed milk over cake.
Allow to set overnight.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle frozen coconut over Cool Whip.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread and raisins in greased 2-quart dish. Combine sugar, eggs, cinnamon and salt. Stir in milk.
Pour over bread and raisins.
Stir.
Let stand 5 minutes. Set dish in shallow pan on oven rack. Add 1-inch water.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Chop garlic fine.
Add salt and basil and mash into paste. Rub pork chops with the paste and leave for 1 hour.

title: baked rigatoni with meatballs
directions: Separate the garlic cloves from the bulb.
Peel and finely chop the garlic.
Chop the basil leaves.
Cut the cores from fresh tomatoes and score an "x" on the base of each.
Immerse them, a few at a time, in a saucepan of boiling water until skins start to split, 8 to 15 seconds.
Transfer the tomatoes to a bowl of cold water.
When cold, peel off the skins.
Cut tomatoes crosswise in half; squeeze out the seeds, then coarsely chop each half.
If using canned tomatoes, chop them, reserving their juice.
Put the tomatoes with any juice, in the frying pan and add 2/3 of the garlic, the basil and a pinch of salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, 10 to 12 minutes; there should be some liquid left in the pan.
Transfer the sauce to a food processor and puree.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and set aside.
Wipe the frying pan clean.
Strip the parsley leaves from the stems and chop.
Put the beef, 1/4 of the Parmesan, chopped parsley leaves, remaining garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Add the egg.
Mix ingredients in the bowl with your hands until they are thoroughly combined.
Fry a small amount of the mixture to test for seasoning; adjust if necessary.
Heat remaining oil in frying pan.
Add the meat after shaping into meatballs about 3/4 inch in diameter.
Make sure the pan is not overcrowded.
Fry the meatballs briskly, until brown on outside and still pink inside, 2 to 4 minutes.
Transfer to large plate and set aside.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Cook and drain eggplant.
Mash and mix all other ingredients. Make into patties and brown in oil in skillet or bake on cookie sheet until done.
Serves 6.

title: easy lemon bars
directions: With a spoon, stir together cake mix and pie filling.
Pour into ungreased jelly roll pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: In small bowl beat together cream cheese and sugars.
Stir in yogurt and drained pineapple.
Spoon into 10 paper bake cups in muffin pans.
Combine pecans and cherries; spoon a little atop each cup.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cajun stuffed egg
directions: Peel eggs.
Slice in half.
Remove egg yolks. Set aside whites.
Mix ham, egg yolks, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix together until well mixed.
Add as much hot sauce as can be tolerated. Spoon into egg whites.
