Serve on a platter with lettuce and cherry tomatoes.

title: busy day dessert
directions: Coat small cake pan with butter or margarine.
Do not flour. Put in can of pie filling, spreading over bottom.
Add dry cake mix.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Fruity good and easy.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Chop pimentos, green pepper, celery and onion.
Thaw peas. Mix all together and let marinate 24 hours.

title: pimento corn soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn; cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in chicken broth and pepper.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in milk; cook until thoroughly heated. (Do not boil.)
Add pimento; stir well.
Ladle soup into bowls. Sprinkle with paprika.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Spoon into 3 well-greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: strawberry bavarian cream
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package. Add strawberries to Jell-O; let set. Beat Jell-O with a beater; add whipped cream. Add marshmallows and bananas.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the macaroni in salted water until firm and tender.
Wash macaroni in cold water.
When completely cool, add all other ingredients.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald 1 3/4 cups milk with chocolate and Karo into top of double boiler.
Blend cornstarch with remaining milk.
Mix in sugar and salt. Add egg yolks and beat until well blended.
Add all at once to scalded chocolate milk. Stir constantly until thickened. Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes longer. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Cool.
Pour into baked shell. Top with meringue. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until meringue is golden.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put butter, water and cocoa in pan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, sugar and soda.
Stir into hot mixture the eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into oblong pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken bog
directions: Wash chicken.
Cook chicken in covered pot approximately 1 hour.
Debone chicken.
Put back in pot.
Add salt and pepper. Add white and yellow rice.
Cook on medium high until rice dries out.
Cover; turn down on low heat for 10 minutes.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Spread topping on bottom of pie crust.
Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with whisk for 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and toffee bars.
Spoon in crust. Freeze 4 hours until set.

title: blueberry lemon bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Add alternately with milk flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom of pan and 1/2-inch up sides to form crust. Seal perforations. Brown sausage; drain. Spread over crusts. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft but not browned; add fresh cabbage, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
When cooked, mix with noodles which have been prepared according to package directions and set aside.
When served, add a dollop of sour cream, if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook with parsley and onion until vegetables are tender.
Drain off water.
Add milk and 1/2 stick of butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Amount of milk added depends on desired consistency of soup.)
Simmer 30 minutes or so to heat thoroughly and blend flavors.
Serve with crackers and sliced Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in greased casserole dish.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with almonds the last 15 minutes.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with turkey.
In saucepan, melt butter, blend in flour and seasoning.
Add broth, cook and stir until thickened. Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs, then pour into hot mixture while beating.
Pour over turkey. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into squares.
Serve with sauce.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add apple slices.
Cover with sugar. Cook uncovered, stirring frequently until apples are tender and clear looking.
Syrup will be thick.

title: blackberry mustard
directions: Put berries in food processor.
Blend about 1 minute or until smooth.
Strain and discard seeds.
Combine with remaining ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Serve with grilled or roasted meats.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator up to two weeks.

title: spiced almonds
directions: Beat egg white until foamy. Add almonds, tossing to coat. In a small bowl, combine sugar, ground cinnamon, ground allspice, seasoned salt and nutmeg. Toss with almonds to coat. Spread almonds on greased baking sheet in single layer. Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour. Cool slightly and break apart. Cool completely. Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
This makes a very large batch of cookies.

title: no bake pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
When thick, add pineapple, pecans, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and bananas.
Pour into pie crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Put half of beans in bowl.
Put half of sugar and mustard. Mix over the beans.
Pour in remaining beans and sprinkle with remaining mixture.
Put pieces of bacon on top and cover with catsup.
Bake at 325°, about 3 hours.

title: (no bake) tyrolean fruit cake
directions: Oil the mold with salad oil or vegetable shortening.
Combine orange juice and gelatin in pan and heat over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Add sugar, molasses, spices and orange rind and beat at high speed 15 minutes until very creamy.
Combine Brazil nuts, raisins, glaced fruit, cherries and graham crackers in large bowl.
Combine creamy mixture with dry mixture and mix well. You may have to use your hands to do this.
Firmly press the fruit cake into the mold.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
To unmold, dip mold into hot water and invert over serving platter.
Garnish mold with glaced pineapple and cherries.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cinnamon, in a large bowl until blended.
Pour into an oblong baking dish. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: creamy chicken-vegetable chowder
directions: Using all soups undiluted and all vegetables undrained. Combine first 9 ingredients in a Dutch oven, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Remove from heat; add cheese, stirring until cheese melts. Garnish if desired and serve immediately.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve in hollowed rye bread.

title: mexican pepper casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice peppers into thin strips.
Heat oil and margarine in heavy skillet; saute onions and garlic with salt and spices until onions are transparent.
Add peppers; cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Sprinkle in flour; mix well.
Continue cooking until liquid is absorbed.
Butter deep casserole; spread half the pepper mixture, top with cheese.
Repeat.
Mix eggs with sour cream; pour over all.
Sprinkle with more paprika.
Bake covered 40 to 45 minutes; uncover last 15 minutes.

title: ham salad
directions: Drain ham.
Work chunks out with fork.
Add celery, onion and enough mayonnaise to make a spreadable mixture (approximately 1/2 cup).
Easy and tasty.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar gradually so it will almost dissolve. Add slowly (gently) bourbon to which has been added gin, vodka and Scotch.
Whip the cream to stiff peaks.
Whip whites of 6 eggs and stir in slowly, but well, until whites seem to disappear.
Let age for 2 days before serving.
Relax and enjoy.

title: hot garlic-herb bread
directions: Cut the bread diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Blend the butter, 1 tablespoon parsley, oregano, dill and garlic.
Put the bread slices together again after putting the butter mixture on each slice.
Shape aluminum foil around the bread in a boat like fashion, twisting the ends and leaving the top open.
Spread a small amount of the butter mixture on top of bread, then sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese and the 1 tablespoon parsley.
Heat in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: buffet beans
directions: Heat green beans
in
their liquid.
Meanwhile, fry the bacon until crisp.
Remove
bacon from skillet and to the fat, add vinegar and
sugar.
Drain beans and arrange in casserole. Top with
onion
slices
and
crumbled	bacon;	pour
vinegar mixture over beans and
let
stand	3 to 4 hours.
Warm before serving.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Clean and cut up veggies in bite size pieces.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse in cold water.
In a big bowl, combine noodles, veggies and cheese.
Apply Italian dressing.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: apple nut cookies
directions: Peel, core and crush apples.
Mix apples, nuts, sugar, shortening and egg in large bowl.
Sift flour, powder and soda. Stir in all ingredients.

title: strawberry layers
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole pan, cover bottom with pieces of angel food cake. Next, spread the pie filling over the cake, then layer the strawberries on the filling.
Last, spread on the Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture.
If desired, garnish with whipped cream and fresh strawberries.

title: peppery pork chops
directions: In a small mixing bowl combine paprika, garlic salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Rub each chop with paprika mixture.
Place the pork chops on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from the heat for 8 minutes.
Turn chops and broil for 7 to 9 minutes more or until the meat is no longer pink.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Separate dinner rolls top from bottom with knife.
Pour melted butter on the inside of rolls.
On bottom halves of rolls, spread on mustard, cheese, ham, cheese, mustard and garlic salt.
Cover and place in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Add flour sifted with soda, baking powder and salt. Add oatmeal, corn flakes and coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven.

title: crab-chas-dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together, except wine.
Place in buttered casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve on Triscuits.
Open wine. "Oh!
I'm in Heaven."

title: tasty crab spread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or thin party rye bread.
If you want to add color, you can add chopped black olives or chopped pimentos.

title: german pork chops
directions: Sprinkle skillet with salt and brown chops.
Arrange potato slices in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Top with kraut. Sprinkle caraway over.
Put chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fruit sherbet - a summer delight
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
When serving, thaw enough to get out of bowl.
Place in compotes or glasses and pour ginger ale over frozen fruit.
Top with a maraschino cherry.
Use any fruit you wish in fruit base.
Serve with cake or cookies.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix melted oleo, sugar and pretzels in 9 x 13-inch dish. Press flat in dish and bake 8 minutes at 400°.

title: squash bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Coat 9 x 13 baking dish with non stick spray.
In a large sauce pan, cook the squash and onions in the water over medium heat for about 15 minutes, or until tender.
Drain well.
In a medium bowl, combine drained squash mixture, soup, cheese, salt, and pepper. Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until heated through, and the topping is golden.

title: chili-cheese spuds
directions: Scrub potatoes and shake to remove excess moisture (don't dry). Place damp potatoes in an electric slow cooker. Cover with lid; cook on low heat setting until potatoes are tender (about 6 to 8 hours; great for the working person). Heat chili. Split open each potato, fluff pulp with a fork. Spoon about 1/2 cup chili into center of each potato, top with 2 tablespoons cheese, 1 tablespoon sour cream and 1 tablespoon green onions.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Place pineapple in buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine sugar and flour; sprinkle over cheese.
Mix crumbled crackers and melted butter; place over top of casserole. Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Mix all at once.
Cook until soft ball forms in cold water. Beat; pour in buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; Drain fat and then add the sauce. Stir well and pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle cheeses over sauce mixture reserving about 1/4 c. of the parmesan cheese for last. Open crescent rolls and lay on top of cheese and pinch seams together.
If they break apart during baling, it doesn't matter because you spoon it out onto the plates.
Sprinkle with remaining parmesan cheese and bake at
for about 15 minutes or until the crescent rolls are browned.
This is good served with a garden salad.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of the juice.
Mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to salmon juice (this is the important secret).
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form immediately into small patties and fry to golden brown in hot oil.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Blend flour, cornstarch, salt and sugar in saucepan.
Stir in milk and add chocolate.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir a couple tablespoons of this chocolate mixture into your egg yolks.
Return egg yolks and chocolate to the remaining chocolate mixture and stir constantly for 2 minutes; add vanilla and pour into a baked pie shell.
Cool in refrigerator and cover with chocolate Cool Whip before serving.

title: tamale pie
directions: Measure cornmeal, water and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Boil until mixture begins to thicken, then add milk.
Continue cooking slowly for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Add onion, tomatoes, pimentos and spices.
Line a baking dish with 3/4 of the cornmeal mush.
Pour beef mixture in dish.
Cover with remaining mush.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baba irena's medivnyk
directions: Preheat oven to 325°; oil small rectangular loaf pans and dust with flour.
In small bowl, beat all egg whites until stiff; set aside.
In large bowl, beat together honey, oil and sugar until mixture is very smooth.
Add yolks one at a time.
Alternate addition of flour and egg whites.
Pour into pans and bake for approximately 50 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased baking dish. Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Mix together eggs, squash and oil. In	another
bowl
beat eggs.
Stir in zucchini and oil. Stir
egg mixture all at once into dry ingredients (which have been
blended together) just until flour is moistened.
Batter will
be
lumpy. Pour
into	18 greased muffin cups.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese pie(quiche)
directions: Mix flour through cheese.
Mix cream and milk with eggs.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then turn oven to 325° and bake 25 or 30 minutes more.

title: cardamon gift bread
directions: Will also need decorative ribbon.

title: fried chicken
directions: Chop garlic fairly fine.
In a small dish, mix the garlic with a sprinkle of salt and puree it.
It will mash better when mixed with salt.
Make a mixture of the eggs, baking powder, garlic, olive oil and cayenne pepper.
Salt and pepper the chicken pieces and stir into the egg mixture.
Allow the chicken to marinate a few hours, turning occasionally.
After chicken has marinated, remove from the egg mixture and roll each piece in flour that has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Heat the shortening or peanut oil in a skillet and when very hot, fry chicken over low heat until good and brown.
With a well tossed salad, a wonderful chicken that will delight your appetite.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies, mix with butter.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer remaining ingredients in order given, freeze after each layer, about 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Add all other ingredients, adding nuts and raisins last.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes until done.

title: jello chiffon
directions: Make Jell-O.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Before it sets, mix in 1/2 cup powdered milk.
Whip up and pour into a bowl to set. Once set, add 8 ounces Cool Whip spread over Jell-O.
Garnish with fruit same as Jell-O (strawberries, mandarin oranges, etc.).

title: sauerkraut
directions: Cut cabbage or shred it.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Fill with water (warm) and seal.
Let stand for a couple of weeks, then cold pack.
Pints take 15 minutes.
Quarts take 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Combine stuffing and beef broth in large bowl.
Add parsley, ground chuck, Parmesan cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly until well blended.
Shape into a loaf and place in a shallow baking pan.	Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over the top and sprinkle with oregano.
Continue baking for 30 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy peanut butter and chocolate cookies
directions: Make sandwiches with peanut butter and crackers.
Melt chocolate in microwave until hot.
Using tongs, dip sandwich in chocolate; let dry thoroughly on wax paper (you must use wax paper to keep from sticking).
Refrigerate to harden.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer(can be made early; cook when ready)
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple cake
directions: Place eggs, orange juice, vanilla, oil and 2 cups sugar in large mixer bowl.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder in large bowl.
Turn mixer on low to start; increase speed to moderate. Beat for 10 minutes.
Cut each apple quarter into 3 slices.
Spoon half the flour mixture into greased and floured tube pan; arrange half the apple slices over.
Sprinkle with half the 4 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Add remaining batter, apples and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan before turning out.

title: dirt cake
directions: In food processor (or any other method), crush Oreos with cream.

title: bridal oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk 1 hour.
Add egg and beat well. Add sugar and then flour, which has been mixed with other dry ingredients.
Mix well and add melted butter.
Bake in greased muffin pans in hot 400° oven for 12 to 18 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pam spray an 8-inch square pan.
Melt oleo; add sugar.
Remove from heat when blended.
Stir in cocoa and vanilla.
Add Egg Beaters.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes or until edge pulls away from sides.
Do not overbake. Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.
Yields 9 to 12 squares.

title: never fail oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and mix rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: horseradish cheese spread
directions: Mash Roquefort cheese with chopped parsley, pimento and a little cream.
Season with Tabasco.
Fill individual stalks of celery with cheese mixture.
Garnish with parsley or pimento.
The spread is good on crackers, also.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Combine coconut, nuts, raisins and fruit with 1 cup flour. Mix well. In a large bowl, cream butter and eggs together. Sift together remaining 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture along with fruit juice and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Stir in nuts and fruit. Mix well. Pour into buttered tube pan. Bake in oven at 250° for 2 1/4 hours.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt margarine and add cocoa and water in a large saucepan. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 25 minutes at 325° in 11 x 17 x 1 in. greased sheet pan.

title: vegetarian "meat" balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
In a skillet, heat 1 to 2 tablespoons light oil.
Form mixture into balls. Saute balls in skillet until light brown.
Add to marinara sauce or sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve with pasta.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Stir 1 cup of sugar into potatoes.
Dissolve yeast in water. Add melted butter or margarine, salt and beaten eggs.
Stir well. Add flour and mix well.
Let rise until doubled.
Spread evenly in 4 greased pans (8 x 8-inch).
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch evenly spaced holes in dough (9 holes per pan).
Put small slice of butter in each hole and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: chicken stew
directions: Saute vegetables in a small amount of oil in a large stew pot. Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Do not add any more liquid.
Great over rice or noodles.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Saute onions in 3 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Remove onions from skillet.
Add 2 more tablespoons of butter and melt. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add half and half and cook over low heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Place onions, cooked celery and pecans in alternate layers in buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with cream sauce; sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and hot.
Serves 6.

title: shredded cabbage soup
directions: Cook and stir onions in fat or margarine in Dutch oven until tender.
Add beef broth, cabbage, potatoes, carrots and celery. Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Garnish each serving with dollop of sour cream and sprinkle of dill weed.

title: easy tomato-cheese macaroni
directions: Heat soup, milk and 1 1/2 cups of cheese over low heat.
When cheese melts, add parsley.
Blend with macaroni.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and buttered crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes in hot oven (400°).
Makes 6 servings.

title: quickie chicken pie
directions: Put meat in bottom of small casserole dish.
Pour margarine over chicken.
Layer with eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over eggs.
Mix soup and broth in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Make well in middle.
Add eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Stir until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: mustard chops with rice
directions: Brush mustard over both sides of pork chops.
Coat with flour. Brown in oil in skillet.
Place rice in a 9 x 15-inch baking dish and top with pork chops.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Mix chicken and rice soup with 1 soup can water in bowl.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until pork chops are tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: mock lobster
directions: DO NOT THAW HADDOCK!!
Cut in half, put frozen fish in 1 qt. water, with sugar, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil. Boil for 10 minutes.
Drain fish well, then sprinkle with paprika and broil for 3 minutes.
Dip in butter and serve.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Soften
butter; add sugar and eggs.
Blend.
Add vanilla. Alternate
flour
and whipping cream.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: punched lemon cake
directions: Mix together 10 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in a large pan at 300° for 35 to 50 minutes.

title: northern baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, drain grease reserving about 2 teaspoons.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add onion, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and garlic salt to frying pan.
Cook until onions are soft and liquid forms a syrup consistency (approx. 5 minutes) over medium heat. Put beans in a 2 quart baking dish.
Add bacon.
Pour onion mixture over beans, mix gently.
Bake in pre-heated 350 oven for 30 minutes or until thoroughly warmed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and drained, crushed pineapple. Stir together sour cream and confectioners sugar; add to fruit mixture. Line
a
cup refrigerator tray with foil; pour in fruit mixture.
Freeze firm.
To serve, turn out frozen salad and let stand a few minutes at room temperature.
Remove foil and cut salad in six wedges.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
I use fat free sour cream and reduced fat mayonnaise and it makes a low-fat dip for just about anything.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump each ingredient (except Cool Whip) in the order given into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: chili rice
directions: Bring rice and water to boil; then let boil on low heat for 20 minutes. Combine cheese, sour cream and chilies in mixing bowl. Butter the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish. Add rice to mix and put in casserole dish. Add a couple pats of butter on top of rice. Microwave 10-15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	slightly,
but	not done.
Drain.
Cook rice in	2
cups
water.
Saute	onion
in margarine.
Combine broccoli, soup, milk, onion, half the cheese, salt and pepper. Pour over
rice
in baking dish and top with remaining cheese. Bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a pie plate.
Cook and stir the ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in the salt and pepper.
Spread into pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour on top of ground beef.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted into center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Wash and separate flowerets on cauliflower.
Trim away any woody part of stem; simmer in salted water about 15 minutes. Drain.
Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Place cauliflower in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over the top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top and then drizzle on melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine mushrooms, onion, garlic and margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave at High (100%) until mushrooms and onions are tender, 2 to 4 minutes.
Shake beef, flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag until beef is coated.
Stir beef and remaining ingredients, except sour cream, in vegetable mixture. Microwave, covered, at high (100%) for 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium-high (70%).
Microwave until beef is tender, 20 to 30 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream until well blended.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bigos(hunter's dish)
directions: Cut sauerkraut several times.
Cover with water and parboil in uncovered pot.
Rinse cabbage and shred.
Cover with small amount of water; add mushrooms and garlic and cook in uncovered pot. Rinse pork; cut into cubes.
Salt and saute in fat until brown. Add to sauerkraut and add seasoning.
Cook slowly.
Cut bacon into cubes; melt the cubes without browning.
Add to sauerkraut. Remove skin from sausage and cut into large cubes.
When sauerkraut and meat are cooked, add sausage and cooked cabbage. Cook sliced onion in fat; add flour and prepare roux (cooked flour and fat mixture used as thickening agent).
Garnish bigos with the roux and season to taste.
Cook on slow fire.
There should be very little sauce in the Bigos.

title: chili
directions: In a large pot, brown meat.
Add salt, pepper, flour and onion.
Cook until onion in translucent. Add chili beans, tomato sauce, garlic powder and chili powder; mix well.
Add water and continue cooking for 1 hour.

title: dad's favorite casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Add undiluted soups and chow mein noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: celery-dill pickles
directions: Take medium to large cucumbers.
Cut lengthwise.
Soak several hours (3 to 4) in cold water and then drain.
Use either celery or slices of onions with as much dill as you wish, or dill can be used alone.
Pack in jars.
Heat vinegar, sugar, water and salt.
Boil well.
Pour over pickles hot.
Drain; reheat and pour over pickles again.
Seal.
This juice is enough for about 2 quarts.
Sometimes, I do not drain the juice; heat and pour over pickles again.
The pickles turn out great and this recipe using celery and dill has been passed on to many people.
Use hot water bath until pickles turn color.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When done, poke holes in top of cake and pour 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, mixed with 1/3 cup lemon juice.

title: diet baked carrot squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cream with the butter.
Add egg, carrot and raisins; mix well.
Pour into 8-inch pan (greased). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in regular oven or 15 minutes in convection oven.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches, juice and water in 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Add half of sugar and half of margarine to peaches.
Put in oven until peaches begin to bubble, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesy potato loaf
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter and add onion. Saute until tender.
Blend in flour, mustard, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk.
Heat to boiling while stirring constantly. Continue to boil and stir
1 minute.
Stir in hash brown potatoes and parsley.

Remove from heat and pack potato mixture into buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Remove from refrigerator and turn out onto baking sheet. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil water.
Add cloves, cinnamon and tea leaves.
Remove from heat and steep for 5 minutes.
Strain.
Heat lemon juice, orange juice and sugar to boil.
Add to hot tea.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken in the corn
directions: Season chicken with salt and flour.
Brown in butter, then remove when brown.
Saute onion and green peppers until soft, then add seasoning, bouillon and corn.
Place chicken in casserole with corn mixture and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add cold water. Blend and cook until clear, not more than 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Blend in lemon juice and a few drops of red food coloring.
Pour glaze over strawberries and gently blend.
Serve in a baked pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: two hour rolls
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add boiling water.
Beat and add the eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix flour and salt with other ingredients to make dough.
Let rise 1 hour.
Shape into rolls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Let rise 1 more hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana split homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed, until frothy. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Add 6 cups milk and salt, mix well.
Pour egg mixture into quite large saucepan over medium heat, cook while stirring constantly until thoroughly heated.
Combine egg mixture, sweetened condensed milk, half and half and vanilla; stir well.
Add 2 bananas, cherries and about 4 oz. of crushed pineapple (more at this time collects heavily on the beater).
Pour mixture into one gallon freezer, electric or hand cranked.
Freeze according to freezer instructions (don't forget your ice and freeze salt) until mixture is in the beginning stage of setting up, yet will easily mix in remaining two bananas and pineapple.
Check beater before ice cream is finally hard with long spoon to ensure all is mixed well.
A real taste and color delight with the red and yellow on white!!
Serves 16.

title: taco dip
directions: In skillet, brown chopped meat, adding seasoning packet. Drain excess oil.
Let cool!

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and melted butter.
Add flour and meal; cream again, then add egg yolks, then vinegar, milk and flavoring.
Beat with mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until mixture thickens or about 30 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs.
Cut lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks.
Mash them with a fork.
Mix in mayo, mustard, pepper and salt.
Fill whites with mixture, heaping it lightly.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serves 6.

title: pete's chicken delicious
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone.
Cut into large pieces. Reserve broth.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion in margarine. Add to stuffing; mix well.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with 1/2 of the cornbread mixture.
Combine soups and broth; pour over cornbread mixture.
Top with remaining 1/2 of cornbread mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: purple pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of cooking oil. Mix blackberry jam and mustard. Spoon jam and mustard mixture over chops. Cover and cook over low heat for approximately 15 to 20 minutes. Spoon sauce over chops and serve. The sauce is also good over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: cherry brunch ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 12-cup fluted tube pan. Place brown sugar, cherry halves, chopped nuts and 1/4 cup melted butter in bottom of pan.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip one side of each biscuit into remaining butter and then into cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place 10 biscuits, coating side down, in prepared pan, overlapping slightly.
Repeat with remaining 10 biscuits to form second layer.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes and then invert onto serving plate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey cutlets
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray rack of foil-lined pan with vegetable oil cooking spray or oil lightly.
In shallow dish, combine uncooked oat bran, parsley, orange peel and sage; mix well.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Combine meat and onion with noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup water, green pepper, chili sauce, pimento, salt and dash of pepper.
Mix well.

title: bul-ko-ki(charcoal beef korean style)
directions: Slice beef into 2 x 1-inch strips.
Combine all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour over beef and mix. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: green onion salad
directions: In food processor, put first 4 ingredients. Blend until smooth. Chill until slightly thickened. Add celery and onions; mix and return to refrigerator until set.

title: cottage cheese zeppelins(varskes cepelinai)
directions: Mix together by hand the grated and mashed potatoes.
With a large glass dipped in flour, cut into round or oval shaped pieces. Combine cheese, egg, salt and caraway seed.
Place a generous tablespoon on each round.
Fold over, press edges together and shape into an oval shaped dumpling.
Boil in rapidly boiling salted water for about 15 minutes.
Lift out with slotted spoon. Serve with melted butter or sour cream.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and put in Pyrex dish. Crush crackers and melt butter. Mix crackers and butter. Spread over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter; mix dressing and remaining ingredients (except soup).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before cooking.
Cover with mushroom soup (undiluted).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325° with foil cover.
Add cheese and bake about 10 minutes longer.

title: orange julius
directions: Place ingredients in blender and process.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread(this is spicy gingerbread)
directions: Beat egg, sugar and Crisco until smooth.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Add buttermilk and molasses.
Roll out on floured cookie sheet.
I pinch them like homemade biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chunky onion dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve as dip for raw vegetables.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil over high heat for 3 minutes.
Add vegetables and stir-fry 3 minutes longer.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over chicken and vegetables. Bring to a boil.
Stir 2 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: pancho's cheese dip
directions: Melt cheeses together. Add remaining ingredients except water. Remove from heat. Mixture will be lumpy. When cool, put in blender and add water.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight canister.
Place 1/4 or 1/3 cup of mix in mug.
Add hot water; mix well (1 cup).

title: mississippi suicide
directions: Cook brownies and cool; break apart.
Put 1 layer in large bowl; top with part of prepared pudding.
Top with part of Cool Whip.
Continue layers.
Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough out on cookie sheet or in pizza pan.
Bake until done.
Let cool.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and nondairy whipped topping together, spread on cookie dough.
Mix strawberries with glaze.
Spread over cream cheese
mixture.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef in large, heavy kettle; drain fat.
Add onion and cook and stir until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with sprinkle of grated cheese on top, if desired.

title: speedy mushroom sauce
directions: Just mix in blender or shaker.
Excellent for steaks or fish. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, basting every 15 minutes or so.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a 7-inch flower pot or 10 small flower pots.

title: pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or rub with fingertips until the shortening particles are the size of peas.
Add milk slowly, tossing mixture lightly.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Add vanilla. Pour over cereal.
Add sugar.
Stir.

title: dove casserole
directions: Soak doves in salt water about 2 hours.
Mix sour cream, soup and seasonings.
Arrange doves in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over doves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Pour wine over doves about 10 minutes before done.
Quail can be substituted for doves.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients until mixed well.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: sicilian meat roll by gini
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except ham and cheese, to form a ball and place on waxed paper.
Flatten out to about 8 x 12 inches.
Place thin slices of ham (about 6) on meat mixture and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up, seal seams and ends. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or microwave on High for 12 to 13 minutes.
Melt more cheese on top the last few minutes if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Microwave broccoli for 4 minutes.
In large bowl, combine soup, milk, water and rice.
Drain broccoli and add to mixture.
Add onions and butter.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana boats
directions: Cut V-shape wedge the length of each banana.
Place banana on double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Stuff bananas with chips and marshmallows.
Wrap securely.
Cook over coals 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crispy chicken with parmesan tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix bread crumbs, parsley, garlic, 2 teaspoons olive or salad oil and 1/4 teaspoon pepper until blended.
Brush mustard onto chicken breasts, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in 11 x 7-inch greased baking dish, crumb side up.
Bake chicken for 20 minutes.
Cut each tomato lengthwise in half.
Mix Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Sprinkle mixture over tomatoes.
Add to chicken in baking dish and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, until coating on chicken is crisp and juices run clear.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes and toss with raisins and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Beat together milk, applesauce, egg whites, sugar and vanilla.
Pour mixture over bread cubes and let stand for 25 minutes.
Pour mixture into prepared pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Remove from oven and serve warm.
Yields 10 servings.

title: deer stew
directions: Brown cut up meat in bacon fat.
Add sliced onions and continue to brown.
When nicely browned, stir in flour.
Place in baking dish and add vinegar, ketchup, sugar, salt and pepper. Cover meat with water; bake in 375° oven for 2 to 3 hours or until tender, adding water as needed to keep meat covered.
When done, thicken gravy and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mina's sweet potato pie
directions: Wash thoroughly, peel and boil potatoes.
Mash when done.
Add sugar and eggs and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and beat again.
Pour in uncooked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; cut in the shortening. Add yeast mixture, then buttermilk mixture. Stir well. Knead dough then place in greased bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and place on cooking sheet well greased. Brush tops with marg. and let set out 2 hours before cooking.
Place in cold oven; bake at 450° until brown, then brush with marg. Makes 30 to 36 rolls.

title: hot rolls
directions: Put hot water in bowl.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Beat eggs in this when it cools down.
Add the 1/2 cup warm water with yeast in it.
Add enough flour to knead; set aside to rise to twice its size.
Knead down again.
Make into rolls; let rise again, then bake in a 350° oven.

title: banana pudding(no bake)
directions: To make low-calorie, substitute sugar-free vanilla pudding, lite Cool Whip and nonfat sour cream.

title: cheezy cheese ball
directions: Chop the onion fine; add garlic and parsley.
Add to cream cheese and Cheddar cheese; form into ball.
Roll into crushed walnuts until covered.
Serve with your favorite crackers.
Serves approximately 20 to 25 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer cut-up chicken, sour cream and chicken soup (which have been mixed) and cracker crumbs, ending with cracker crumbs.
Add melted oleo and poppy seed on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: german dressing
directions: Put butter in skillet and melt, cooking celery and onions that have been chopped up.
When slightly brown, add meat.
While cooking or before, put bread that has been slightly toasted, in milk that has been almost boiled.
Pour milk over broken bread pieces and let stand 30 minutes.
Then add all ingredients together.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef and season to taste.
Cut up Velveeta in 1-inch cubes.
Place in microwave safe dish.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes (undrained).
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Add ground beef. Stir and serve with tortilla chips.

title: fish chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, saute onion, carrots and celery in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Add fish, potatoes, bay leaf, salt, thyme, pepper and wine.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
With fork, break fish into chunks.
Add milk and remaining butter.
Discard bay leaf.
Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Add water and shortening.
Add eggs, beating well.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
After cool, remove from pan. Drizzle with glaze made from powdered sugar, lemon juice and butter.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/3 cup butter together.
Beat in milk and eggs.
Fold mixture into a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine coconut, brown sugar, flour, pecans and 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Freezes well.
